"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/229239","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2015-03-26","<p /> <p>The Department does hold information on the duration of benefit sanctions however the specific information requested is not readily available and could only be provided at disproportionate cost.</p>","Wirral West","Esther McVey",,"2015-03-26T09:11:37.363Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/229239/answer","Biography information for Esther McVey","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/229239/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/229239/answer",,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2015-03-23","Social Security Benefits: Disqualification","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, what the longest duration of sanction imposed on a claimant in the work related activity group was in (a) 2013 and (b) 2014.","false","Biography information for Stephen Timms","East Ham","Stephen Timms","228757"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/229240","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2015-03-26","<p>Help to Work was introduced in April 2014. The Department for Work and Pensions intends to publish statistics on Help to Work and we are considering the date for publication.</p>","Wirral West","Esther McVey",,"2015-03-26T09:03:24.673Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/229240/answer","Biography information for Esther McVey","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/229240/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/229240/answer",,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2015-03-23","Employment Schemes","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, how many people have joined each of the three options in the Help to Work programme in each month since May 2014.","false","Biography information for Stephen Timms","East Ham","Stephen Timms","228756"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/229241","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2015-03-26","<p>The Department has not commissioned any research specifically on this topic. We will consider the need to commission any such research alongside future Departmental evidence requirements.</p>","Wirral West","Esther McVey","228752","2015-03-26T08:47:24.063Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/229241/answer","Biography information for Esther McVey","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/229241/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/229241/answer",,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2015-03-23","Employment","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, if he will place in the Library the research his Department has commissioned on links between securing a short-hours job and a subsequent gain of longer-hours jobs.","false","Biography information for Stephen Timms","East Ham","Stephen Timms","228759"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/229242","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2015-03-26","<p>The information we have for Jobseeker’s Allowance and Employment and Support Allowance adverse sanction decisions, by geography and reason, is published at:<br></p><p><a href="https://stat-xplore.dwp.gov.uk/" target="_blank">https://stat-xplore.dwp.gov.uk/</a></p><p><br> Guidance on how to extract the information required can be found at:<br></p><p><a href="https://sw.stat-xplore.dwp.gov.uk/webapi/online-help/Stat-Xplore_User_Guide.htm" target="_blank">https://sw.stat-xplore.dwp.gov.uk/webapi/online-help/Stat-Xplore_User_Guide.htm</a></p>","Wirral West","Esther McVey",,"2015-03-26T08:40:48.933Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/229242/answer","Biography information for Esther McVey","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/229242/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/229242/answer",,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2015-03-23","Social Security Benefits: Disqualification","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, how many benefit sanctions were applied to claimants resident in (a) Airdrie and Shotts constituency, (b) North Lanarkshire, (c) Scotland and (d) the UK in each month since July 2010.","false","Biography information for Pamela Nash","Airdrie and Shotts","Pamela Nash","228741"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/229243","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2015-03-26","<p>I refer the hon. Member to the Written Answer I gave the hon. Member for Rutherglen and Hamilton West, Tom Greatrex, to his question <a href="http://www.parliament.uk/business/publications/written-questions-answers-statements/written-question/Commons/2015-02-04/223341/" target="_blank">UIN 223341</a>, published on the Question and Answer system on 4 February.</p><p> </p><p>Latest Great Britain figures relating to the number of claims disallowed pre-referral to the assessment providers for both PIP new claims and reassessments were published on 18 March as part of our quarterly PIP official statistics release and can be found at <a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/collections/personal-independence-payment-statistics" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/collections/personal-independence-payment-statistics</a>, and in particular table 2Bi of the data tables <a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/uploads/system/uploads/attachment_data/file/412878/tables-pip-statistics-apr-2013-to-jan-2015.xls" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/uploads/system/uploads/attachment_data/file/412878/tables-pip-statistics-apr-2013-to-jan-2015.xls</a>.</p>","Forest of Dean","Mr Mark Harper",,"2015-03-26T08:56:10.73Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/229243/answer","Biography information for Mr Mark Harper","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/229243/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/229243/answer",,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2015-03-23","Personal Independence Payment","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, how many and what proportion of personal independence payment claims in (a) Airdrie and Shotts constituency, (b) North Lanarkshire, (c) Scotland and (d) the UK in each month since April 2013 were disallowed pre-referral to the assessment providers; and how many such claims were disallowed due to the claimant not returning the Part 2 form within the time limit.","false","Biography information for Pamela Nash","Airdrie and Shotts","Pamela Nash","228755"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/229244","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2015-03-26","<p /> <p>The Department has not commissioned any research specifically on this topic. We will consider the need to commission any such research alongside future Departmental evidence requirements.</p>","Wirral West","Esther McVey","228759","2015-03-26T08:47:23.923Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/229244/answer","Biography information for Esther McVey","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/229244/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/229244/answer",,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2015-03-23","Employment","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, what research his Department has commissioned on links between securing a short-hours job and securing a longer-hours job; and if he will make a statement.","false","Biography information for Stephen Timms","East Ham","Stephen Timms","228752"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/229245","Cabinet Office","false","2015-03-26","<p>The information requested falls within the responsibility of the UK Statistics Authority. I have asked the Authority to reply.</p><p> </p>","Reading East","Mr Rob Wilson",,"2015-03-26T09:23:17.44Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/229245/answer","Biography information for Mr Rob Wilson","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/229245/answer","PQ 228670 ONS121.pdf","PQ 228670 ONS121.pdf","ONS Letter to Member - Jobseekers Allowance","ONS Letter to Member - Jobseekers Allowance","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/229245/answer",,,,,"53","Cabinet Office","Cabinet Office","2015-03-23","Jobseeker's Allowance: North East","1","House of Commons","To ask the Minister for the Cabinet Office, with reference to the ONS nomis database, of the 5,030 people in the North East who ceased to claim jobseeker's allowance in January 2015 for other reasons, how many (a) ceased claiming, (b) failed to sign, (c) went on to full-time education, (d) went abroad, (e) reached retirement age, (f) passed away and (g) did so for unknown reasons.","false","Biography information for Alex Cunningham","Stockton North","Alex Cunningham","228670"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/229246","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2015-03-26","<p>The ESA 50 is completed by claimants with help from a friend, relative, carer or representative such as a support worker if needed.</p><p> </p><p><a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/uploads/system/uploads/attachment_data/file/408008/esa-50-capability-for-work-questionnaire.pdf" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/uploads/system/uploads/attachment_data/file/408008/esa-50-capability-for-work-questionnaire.pdf</a></p><p> </p><p>Therefore no training is required or provided to GPs and other healthcare professions on completing it.</p><p> </p><p>Guidance and information for GPs and other healthcare professionals from the DWP can be found at:</p><p> </p><p><a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/collections/healthcare-practitioners-guidance-and-information-from-dwp" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/collections/healthcare-practitioners-guidance-and-information-from-dwp</a></p>","Forest of Dean","Mr Mark Harper",,"2015-03-26T09:22:30.033Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/229246/answer","Biography information for Mr Mark Harper","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/229246/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/229246/answer",,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2015-03-23","Employment and Support Allowance","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, what training is provided to GPs and other healthcare professions on completing the ESA 50 form; and what steps his Department is taking to monitor and update that training.","false","Biography information for Joan Walley","Stoke-on-Trent North","Joan Walley","228688"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/229247","Cabinet Office","false","2015-03-26","<p>The information requested falls within the responsibility of the UK Statistics Authority. I have asked the Authority to reply.</p><p> </p>","Reading East","Mr Rob Wilson",,"2015-03-26T09:22:05.133Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/229247/answer","Biography information for Mr Rob Wilson","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/229247/answer","PQ 228831 ONS 119.pdf","PQ 228831 ONS 119.pdf","ONS Letter to Member - Median Income","ONS Letter to Member - Median Income","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/229247/answer",,,,,"53","Cabinet Office","Cabinet Office","2015-03-23","Personal Income: Blackpool","1","House of Commons","To ask the Minister for the Cabinet Office, what the median income from work was of residents of Blackpool South constituency in (a) 2010, (b) 2011, (c) 2012, (d) 2013, (e) 2014 and (f) 2015 to date.","false","Biography information for Gordon Marsden","Blackpool South","Mr Gordon Marsden","228831"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/229248","Cabinet Office","false","2015-03-26","<p>The information requested falls within the responsibility of the UK Statistics Authority. I have asked the Authority to reply.</p><p> </p>","Reading East","Mr Rob Wilson",,"2015-03-26T09:23:44.2Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/229248/answer","Biography information for Mr Rob Wilson","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/229248/answer","PQ 228832 ONS 120.pdf","PQ 228832 ONS 120.pdf","ONS Letter to Member - Living Wage","ONS Letter to Member - Living Wage","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/229248/answer",,,,,"53","Cabinet Office","Cabinet Office","2015-03-23","Pay: Blackpool","1","House of Commons","To ask the Minister for the Cabinet Office, what proportion of people in employment in Blackpool South constituency were earning (a) the minimum wage or below and (b) the living wage or below in (i) 2010, (ii) 2011, (iii) 2012, (iv) 2013, (v) 2014 and (vi) 2015.","false","Biography information for Gordon Marsden","Blackpool South","Mr Gordon Marsden","228832"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/229249","Department for Communities and Local Government","false","2015-03-26","<p>It has not proved possible to respond to the hon. Member in the time available before Prorogation.</p>","Keighley","Kris Hopkins",,"2015-03-26T08:34:13.353Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/229249/answer","Biography information for Kris Hopkins","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/229249/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/229249/answer",,,,,"7","Communities and Local Government","Communities and Local Government","2015-03-23","Research","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Communities and Local Government, what research reports his Department has commissioned from external bodies between September 2010 and December 2014 has not been published; when each such report was commissioned; what the nature of the research commissioned for each such report was; from whom each such research report was commissioned; what the value of each such commission was; on what date each such report was received by his Department; for what reason each such research report has not yet been published; and when he plans to publish each such report.","false","Biography information for Mr Clive Betts","Sheffield South East","Mr Clive Betts","228840"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/229250","Department for Communities and Local Government","false","2015-03-26","<p>The attached table shows the details of the last payment dates for the reports listed in the Written Ministerial Statement of 20 March 2014, HCWS438.</p><p> </p><p>Final payments are associated with the receipt of draft final outputs from research projects. These reports are from research commissioned under the previous administration, and have continued under the current administration. Reports are not published until the research work is complete and final checks are made. This includes quality assurance and in some cases peer review of the final research outputs which inevitably delays the publication process.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p>As I explained in my Statement, this Government inherited £26 million of unpublished research reports from the last Administration. I do not have access to Ministerial papers of the last Administration to ascertain the rationale for this.</p><p><br></p><p>Since 2010 in the interests of transparency, we have been working through the backlog of over 150 unpublished research reports commissioned under the previous Administration. These have been published in groups over this period.<br><br></p><p> </p><p> </p>","Keighley","Kris Hopkins",,"2015-03-26T11:22:32.137Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/229250/answer","Biography information for Kris Hopkins","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/229250/answer","228830 Betts.xlsx","228830 Betts.xlsx","Reports Data","Reports Data","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/229250/answer",,,,,"7","Communities and Local Government","Communities and Local Government","2015-03-23","Research","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Communities and Local Government, pursuant to the Written Statement of 20 March 2014, HCWS438, on what date each of the reports listed was received by his Department; on what date the last payment was made to each research organisation commissioned to produce each of those reports; and for what reason each of those reports had not previously been published.","false","Biography information for Mr Clive Betts","Sheffield South East","Mr Clive Betts","228830"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/229251","Department for Culture Media and Sport","false","2015-03-26","<p>This table shows research commissioned by the Department for Culture, Media and Sport between September 2010 and December 2014 which is yet to be published.</p><p> </p><table><tbody><tr><td><p><strong>Research Title</strong></p></td><td><p><strong>Nature of Research</strong></p></td><td><p><strong>External contractor</strong></p></td><td><p><strong>Value of work</strong></p></td></tr><tr><td><p>The Local economic impacts from cultural sector investments</p></td><td><p>The purpose of this report is to bring together the best evidence of local economic impacts from culture into one report which could inform the department’s evidence base on the value of culture. The purpose was also to aid others in making the case for culture whether it’s local government, ALBs or the culture sector more widely.</p></td><td><p>ECORYS</p></td><td><p>£20,303</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Publication of Child Taking Part Survey: Multivariate analysis of the determinants of child participation in arts, sport, heritage, museums and libraries.</p></td><td><p>To explore the factors most strongly associated with child participation in arts, sport, heritage, museums and libraries, both in and outside of school. Commissioned by the Culture and Sport Evidence (CASE).</p></td><td><p>Sheffield Hallam University, Sport Industry Research Centre (SIRC)</p></td><td><p>£21,156</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Outlook and structure of publicly funded organisations in culture, heritage and sports</p></td><td><p>Programme of research scoping the extent to which local sport and cultural organisations can be surveyed to provide information on their business practices and underlying attitudes towards ensuring resilience during times of difficult economic operating climate.</p></td><td><p>BOP consulting</p></td><td><p>£79,575</p></td></tr></tbody></table><p> </p><p>The Department has yet to identify appropriate events or publication opportunities for the 3 named pieces of research.</p>","Maidstone and The Weald","Mrs Helen Grant",,"2015-03-26T09:32:15.807Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/229251/answer","Biography information for Mrs Helen Grant","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/229251/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/229251/answer",,,,,"10","Culture, Media and Sport","Culture, Media and Sport","2015-03-23","Research","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Culture, Media and Sport, what research reports his Department has commissioned from external bodies between September 2010 and December 2014 have not been published; when each such report was commissioned; what the nature of the research commissioned for each report was; from whom each such research report was commissioned; what the value of each such commission was; on what date each such report was received by his Department; for what reason each such research report has not yet been published; and when he plans to publish each such report.","false","Biography information for Mr Clive Betts","Sheffield South East","Mr Clive Betts","228819"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/229252","Department for Education","false","2015-03-26","<p>The Department for Education does not hold a record of all visitors. The Department does hold records of visitors who have signed out a temporary pass, which could be searched only at disproportionate cost.</p><p> </p>","Bognor Regis and Littlehampton","Mr Nick Gibb",,"2015-03-26T09:18:40.837Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/229252/answer","Biography information for Nick Gibb","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/229252/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/229252/answer",,,,,"60","Education","Education","2015-03-23","Members","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Education, how many times the right hon. Member for Surrey Heath has visited her Department since 14 July 2014; and what the date was of each such visit.","false","Biography information for Mr Jim Cunningham","Coventry South","Mr Jim Cunningham","228828"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/229253","Department for Education","false","2015-03-26","<p>The Department for Education does not have a full breakdown of revenue spent on staff salaries for proposed free school projects.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p>The total pre-opening expenditure for free school projects that opened or were withdrawn in 2011 to 2013 is published on the Department's website:</p><p><a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/publications/revenue-expenditure-for-free-schools" target="_blank">www.gov.uk/government/publications/revenue-expenditure-for-free-schools</a></p>","Crewe and Nantwich","Mr Edward Timpson",,"2015-03-26T09:48:05.397Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/229253/answer","Biography information for Edward Timpson","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/229253/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/229253/answer",,,,,"60","Education","Education","2015-03-23","Free Schools","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Education, how much her Department has spent since May 2010 on underwriting the salaries of staff at free schools when their school did not open or open on time as planned.","false","Biography information for Mr Jim Cunningham","Coventry South","Mr Jim Cunningham","228829"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/229254","Department for Education","false","2015-03-26","<p>Schools funding data are published annually. This includes data on the number of pupils funded by type of school, so free schools can be identified. The number of pupils enrolled is included in the Census data return, also published annually. The data can be accessed on GOV.UK:</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p>Pre 16 - <a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/publications/schools-block-funding-allocations-2014-to-2015" target="_blank">www.gov.uk/government/publications/schools-block-funding-allocations-2014-to-2015</a></p><p> </p><p>Post 16 - <a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/publications/16-to-19-allocation-data-2014-to-2015-academic-year" target="_blank">www.gov.uk/government/publications/16-to-19-allocation-data-2014-to-2015-academic-year</a></p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p>Schools census data <a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/statistics/schools-pupils-and-their-characteristics-january-2014" target="_blank">www.gov.uk/government/statistics/schools-pupils-and-their-characteristics-january-2014</a></p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p>","Crewe and Nantwich","Mr Edward Timpson",,"2015-03-26T09:52:05.45Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/229254/answer","Biography information for Edward Timpson","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/229254/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/229254/answer",,,,,"60","Education","Education","2015-03-23","Free Schools","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Education, if she will publish a list of free schools indicating how many children have been enrolled at each school and how many pupils are funded at each school.","false","Biography information for Mr Jim Cunningham","Coventry South","Mr Jim Cunningham","228827"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/229255","Department of Health","false","2015-03-26","<p>The following table provided by the Health and Social Care Information Centre (HSCIC) shows the number of finished consultant episodes with a primary or secondary diagnosis of (a) age-related macular degeneration, (b) glaucoma, (c) diabetic retinopathy and (d) cataracts in the National Health Service in England between 2009/10 and 2013/14.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><table><tbody><tr><td><p>Year</p></td><td><p>Age-related Macular Degeneration</p></td><td><p>Glaucoma</p></td><td><p>Diabetic Retinopathy</p></td><td><p>Cataracts</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2009-10</p></td><td><p>100,455</p></td><td><p>95,400</p></td><td><p>63,143</p></td><td><p>381,071</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2010-11</p></td><td><p>128,439</p></td><td><p>123,962</p></td><td><p>77,704</p></td><td><p>390,571</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2011-12</p></td><td><p>138,202</p></td><td><p>133,061</p></td><td><p>78,419</p></td><td><p>389,181</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2012-13</p></td><td><p>149,635</p></td><td><p>139,385</p></td><td><p>80,615</p></td><td><p>395,882</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2013-14</p></td><td><p>152,583</p></td><td><p>156,115</p></td><td><p>93,058</p></td><td><p>437,038</p></td></tr><tr><td><p> </p></td><td><p> </p></td><td><p> </p></td><td><p> </p></td><td><p><strong> </strong></p></td></tr><tr><td colspan="5"><p><em>Source:</em> Hospital Episode Statistics, HSCIC</p></td></tr></tbody></table><p> </p><p><strong> </strong></p><p> </p><p>This data includes patients who were treated as inpatients or day cases (admitted patient care) but not patients who were treated as an outpatient.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p>It should be noted that the data shown above is not a count of people, as the same person may have had an episode of care on more than one occasion within the same year.</p><p> </p>","Battersea","Jane Ellison",,"2015-03-26T14:47:03.837Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/229255/answer","Biography information for Jane Ellison","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/229255/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/229255/answer",,,,,"17","Health","Health","2015-03-23","Visual Impairment","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health, how many finished consultant episodes with a primary or secondary diagnosis of (a) age-related macular degeneration, (b) glaucoma, (c) diabetic retinopathy and (d) cataracts there were in the NHS in England in each of the last five years.","false","Biography information for Liz Kendall","Leicester West","Liz Kendall","228836"
