.5</p></td><td><p>5.6</p></td><td><p>13.2</p></td><td><p>0.9</p></td><td><p>3.9</p></td><td><p>10.2</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>35-39</p></td><td><p>2.9</p></td><td><p>9.3</p></td><td><p>14.8</p></td><td><p>1.5</p></td><td><p>5.1</p></td><td><p>11.2</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>40-44</p></td><td><p>5.9</p></td><td><p>14.6</p></td><td><p>20.8</p></td><td><p>2.2</p></td><td><p>7.8</p></td><td><p>15.9</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>45-49</p></td><td><p>9.6</p></td><td><p>22.0</p></td><td><p>30.4</p></td><td><p>6.4</p></td><td><p>14.9</p></td><td><p>23.3</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>50-54</p></td><td><p>17.4</p></td><td><p>31.6</p></td><td><p>45.1</p></td><td><p>10.7</p></td><td><p>20.8</p></td><td><p>34.2</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>55-59</p></td><td><p>38.6</p></td><td><p>46.7</p></td><td><p>58.5</p></td><td><p>27.8</p></td><td><p>31.9</p></td><td><p>46.5</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>60-64</p></td><td><p>95.9</p></td><td><p>72.3</p></td><td><p>69.9</p></td><td><p>64.2</p></td><td><p>47.5</p></td><td><p>55.2</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>65-69</p></td><td><p>219.9</p></td><td><p>101.2</p></td><td><p>72.5</p></td><td><p>154.0</p></td><td><p>69.6</p></td><td><p>60.5</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>70-74</p></td><td><p>466.5</p></td><td><p>147.9</p></td><td><p>77.0</p></td><td><p>331.3</p></td><td><p>100.6</p></td><td><p>65.9</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>75-79</p></td><td><p>830.2</p></td><td><p>189.2</p></td><td><p>72.5</p></td><td><p>596.0</p></td><td><p>127.6</p></td><td><p>64.4</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>80-84</p></td><td><p>1,362.5</p></td><td><p>203.7</p></td><td><p>57.9</p></td><td><p>942.9</p></td><td><p>138.7</p></td><td><p>52.5</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>85-89</p></td><td><p>1,809.6</p></td><td><p>183.8</p></td><td><p>34.0</p></td><td><p>1,281.0</p></td><td><p>119.5</p></td><td><p>35.4</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>90 and over</p></td><td><p>1,623.6</p></td><td><p>109.5</p></td><td><p>11.5</p></td><td><p>1,239.8</p></td><td><p>69.3</p></td><td><p>13.5</p></td></tr></tbody></table><p> </p><p><em>Source:</em> Hospital Episode Statistics (HES), Health and Social Care Information Centre</p><p> </p><p><strong> </strong></p><p> </p><p>The data includes patients who were treated as inpatients or day cases (admitted patient care) but not patients who were treated as outpatients or in primary care. The rate of these diseases is likely to be much higher as some cases would not require a hospital admission.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p>It should be noted that this is not a count of people as the same person may have had an episode of care on more than one occasion within the same year.</p><p> </p>","Battersea","Jane Ellison",,"2015-03-26T14:48:44.123Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/229256/answer","Biography information for Jane Ellison","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/229256/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/229256/answer",,,,,"17","Health","Health","2015-03-23","Visual Impairment","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health, what the rate was of (a) age-related macular degeneration, (b) glaucoma and (c) diabetic retinopathy per 100,000 population by age group in (i) 2013-14 and (ii) 2014-15 to date.","false","Biography information for Liz Kendall","Leicester West","Liz Kendall","228837"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/229257","Department of Health","false","2015-03-26","<p>The following table provides a count of finished admission episodes where there was a primary or secondary diagnosis of fractures attributable to osteoporosis amongst men, women and genders not specified for the age groups requested for the period 2013-14.</p><p> </p><p><strong> </strong></p><p> </p><table><tbody><tr><td colspan="3"><p>Women</p></td><td colspan="3"><p>Men</p></td><td colspan="3"><p>Unknown gender</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Aged under 50</p></td><td><p>Aged above 50</p></td><td><p>Unknown age</p></td><td><p>Aged under 50</p></td><td><p>Aged above 50</p></td><td><p>Unknown age</p></td><td><p>Aged under 50</p></td><td><p>Aged above 50</p></td><td><p>Unknown age</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>252</p></td><td><p>11,142</p></td><td><p>15</p></td><td><p>237</p></td><td><p>3,232</p></td><td><p>8</p></td><td><p>-</p></td><td><p>3</p></td><td><p>-</p></td></tr></tbody></table><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p><em>Notes:</em></p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p>1. A finished consultant episode (FCE) is a continuous period of admitted patient care under one consultant within one healthcare provider. FCEs are counted against the year in which they end. Figures do not represent the number of different patients, as a person may have more than one episode of care within the same stay in hospital or in different stays in the same year.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p>2. The number of episodes where this diagnosis was recorded in any of the 20 (14 from 2002-03 to 2006-07 and 7 prior to 2002-03) primary and secondary diagnosis fields in a Hospital Episode Statistics (HES) record. Each episode is only counted once, even if the diagnosis is recorded in more than one diagnosis field of the record.</p><p> </p><p><strong> </strong></p><p> </p><p><em>Source:</em> Hospital Episodes Statistics (HES) Health and Social Care Information Centre.</p><p> </p><p><strong> </strong></p><p> </p>","North Norfolk","Norman Lamb",,"2015-03-26T12:53:05.377Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/229257/answer","Biography information for Norman Lamb","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/229257/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/229257/answer",,,,,"17","Health","Health","2015-03-23","Osteoporosis","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health, how many finished hospital admission episodes with a primary or secondary diagnosis of fractures attributable to osteoporosis there were amongst (a) women under, (b) women over, (c) men under and (d) men over the age of 50 in 2013-14.","false","Biography information for Liz Kendall","Leicester West","Liz Kendall","228838"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/229258","Department of Health","false","2015-03-25","<p>The Department funds research through the National Institute for Health Research (NIHR) and the Department’s Policy Research Programme (PRP). The NIHR’s policy statement on open access for its funded research can be found on the NIHR website:</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p><a href="http://www.nihr.ac.uk/policy-and-standards/nihr-policy-on-open-access-for-its-funded-research.htm" target="_blank">http://www.nihr.ac.uk/policy-and-standards/nihr-policy-on-open-access-for-its-funded-research.htm</a></p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p>Details of commissioned and researcher-led projects funded through programmes managed by the NIHR Evaluation, Trials and Studies Coordinating Centre can be found on the centre’s website:</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p><a href="http://www.nets.nihr.ac.uk/projects?collection=netscc&amp;meta_P_sand=Project" target="_blank">http://www.nets.nihr.ac.uk/projects?collection=netscc&amp;meta_P_sand=Project</a></p><p> </p><p><strong> </strong></p><p> </p><p>These details include research summary, contractor, cost, start date, estimated date of publication, and links to commissioning briefs and published reports.</p><p> </p><p><strong> </strong></p><p> </p><p>Details of projects, initiatives and long-term programmes of research currently funded by the PRP are available on the website of the PRP Central Commissioning Facility:</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p><a href="http://www.prp-ccf.org.uk/" target="_blank">http://www.prp-ccf.org.uk/</a></p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p>These details include research summary, contractor, start date, and estimated date of completion. Cost will be included in future updates. The website also has links to summary final reports received since April 2011.</p><p> </p><p><strong> </strong></p><p> </p><p><strong> </strong></p><p> </p>","Mid Norfolk","George Freeman",,"2015-03-25T17:28:13.833Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/229258/answer","Biography information for George Freeman","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/229258/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/229258/answer",,,,,"17","Health","Health","2015-03-23","Research","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health, what research reports his Department has commissioned from external bodies between September 2010 and December 2014 have not been published; when each such report was commissioned; what the nature of the research commissioned for each report was; from whom each such research report was commissioned; what the value of each such commission was; on what date each such report was received by his Department; for what reason each such research report has not yet been published; and when he plans to publish each such report.","false","Biography information for Mr Clive Betts","Sheffield South East","Mr Clive Betts","228818"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/229259","Department of Health","false","2015-03-26","<p>The table below shows how many National Health Service funded sight tests were provided in England to people aged over 60 and to other eligible groups in each of the last five years.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><table><tbody><tr><td><p> </p></td><td><p>2009/10</p></td><td><p>2010/11</p></td><td><p>2011/12</p></td><td><p>2012/13</p></td><td><p>2013/14</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Aged 60 and over</p></td><td><p>5,191,773</p></td><td><p>5,305,177</p></td><td><p>5,537,930</p></td><td><p>5,480,711</p></td><td><p>5,562,847</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Other eligible groups</p></td><td><p>6,619,878</p></td><td><p>6,633,352</p></td><td><p>6,767,797</p></td><td><p>6,858,542</p></td><td><p>7,224,583</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Total</p></td><td><p>11,811,651</p></td><td><p>11,938,529</p></td><td><p>12,305,727</p></td><td><p>12,339,253</p></td><td><p>12,787,430</p></td></tr></tbody></table><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p><em>Source:</em> Health and Social Care Information Centre</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p>Free sight tests on the NHS are available to certain eligible groups including people aged 60 and over, children under 16, those aged 16-18 in full-time education, people on low incomes and defined categories of people at particular risk of developing eye disease.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p>Some individuals may qualify for an NHS sight test on more than one criterion. However, they would only be recorded against one criterion on the NHS sight test form. Patients are more likely to be recorded according to their clinical need rather than their age. For example, a patient aged over 60, with glaucoma is likely to be recorded in the glaucoma category only. The count for those aged 60 and over is therefore an approximate figure and may slightly underestimate.</p><p> </p>","Mid Norfolk","George Freeman",,"2015-03-26T11:14:53.9Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/229259/answer","Biography information for George Freeman","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/229259/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/229259/answer",,,,,"17","Health","Health","2015-03-23","Eyesight: Testing","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health, how many free sight tests were provided on the NHS to people aged (a) under and (b) over 60 in England in each of the last five years.","false","Biography information for Liz Kendall","Leicester West","Liz Kendall","228835"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/229260","Home Office","false","2015-03-26","<p>The Home Office does not collect police workforce statistics for Blackpool South Constituency.<br><br>The Home Office collects and publishes statistics on the police workforce at police force area level but not more locally.<br><br>The table provided contains data on the number of full-time police community support officers (headcount) employed by Lancashire Constabulary as at 31 March 2010 to 31 March 2014. Data for 2015 have not yet been collected centrally and will not be published until later this year.</p><p> </p><p> </p><table><tbody><tr><td colspan="6"><strong>Number of full-time police community support officers (headcount<sup>1</sup>) employed by Lancashire Constabulary as at 31 March 2010 to 31 March 2014<sup>2</sup></strong></td></tr><tr><td> </td><td> </td><td> </td><td> </td><td> </td><td> </td></tr><tr><td> </td><td>2010</td><td>2011</td><td>2012</td><td>2013</td><td>2014</td></tr><tr><td>Lancashire Constabulary</td><td>411</td><td>365</td><td>383</td><td>339</td><td>268</td></tr><tr><td> </td><td> </td><td> </td><td> </td><td> </td><td> </td></tr><tr><td colspan="6">1. These figures are provided on a headcount basis, they represent total number of police community support officers (headcount) less part-time officers (headcount).</td></tr><tr><td colspan="6">2. Police community support officer numbers with full-time/part-time breakdowns, by police force area, are published in the Police Workforce, England and Wales, statistical publications and can be found at: https://www.gov.uk/government/collections/police-workforce-england-and-wales.</td></tr></tbody></table><p> </p><p> </p>","Hemel Hempstead","Mike Penning",,"2015-03-26T10:14:01.53Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/229260/answer","Biography information for Sir Mike Penning","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/229260/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/229260/answer",,,,,"1","Home Office","Home Office","2015-03-23","Police Community Support Officers: Blackpool","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for the Home Department, how many police community support officers were registered full-time in Blackpool South constituency in (a) 2010, (b) 2011, (c) 2012, (d) 2013, (e) 2014 and (f) January to March 2015.","false","Biography information for Gordon Marsden","Blackpool South","Mr Gordon Marsden","228833"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/229261","Home Office","false","2015-03-26","<p>Figures on the number of police officers who took voluntary redundancy or retired before their statutory age are not collected centrally by the Home Office.<br><br>However, the Home Office does collect statistics on the number of voluntary resignations, normal retirements and early medical retirements. Figures are only available at police force level and cannot be broken down further. Data for 2014/15 have not yet been collected centrally and will not be available until later this year.<br><br>The table provided contains data on the number of full-time equivalent police officer voluntary resignations, normal retirements and early medical retirements for Lancashire Constabulary, from 2009/10 to 2013/14.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p>","Hemel Hempstead","Mike Penning",,"2015-03-26T10:13:05.84Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/229261/answer","Biography information for Sir Mike Penning","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/229261/answer","PQ228834_table.xlsx","PQ228834_table.xlsx","Number of police officer voluntary resignations ","Number of police officer voluntary resignations ","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/229261/answer",,,,,"1","Home Office","Home Office","2015-03-23","Police: Blackpool","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for the Home Department, how many police officers (a) took voluntary redundancy, (b) retired before their statutory age in Blackpool in (i) 2010, (ii) 2011, (iii) 2012, (iv) 2013, (v) 2014 and (vi) January to March 2015.","false","Biography information for Gordon Marsden","Blackpool South","Mr Gordon Marsden","228834"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/229262","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2015-03-26","<p>The available information on average (median) clearance times, at a national level, has been published and is available from the Personal Independence Payment statistics home page: <a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/collections/personal-independence-payment-statistics" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/collections/personal-independence-payment-statistics</a>.</p><p> </p><p>The requested level of disaggregation by disabling condition could only be obtained at disproportionate cost.</p>","Forest of Dean","Mr Mark Harper",,"2015-03-26T09:19:07.867Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/229262/answer","Biography information for Mr Mark Harper","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/229262/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/229262/answer",,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2015-03-23","Personal Independence Payment","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, what the average length of time was that his Department took to process a personal independence payment from (a) a motor neurone disease sufferer and (b) another disabled person in the most recent period for which data is available.","false","Biography information for Liz Kendall","Leicester West","Liz Kendall","228839"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/229263","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2015-03-26","<p>I refer the hon. Member to the reply given to the hon. Member for Newcastle upon Tyne North, Catherine McKinnell, on 13 October 2014 to Question UIN <a href="http://www.parliament.uk/business/publications/written-questions-answers-statements/written-questions-answers/?page=1&amp;max=20&amp;questiontype=AllQuestions&amp;house=commons&amp;use-dates=True&amp;answered-from=2014-10-13&amp;answered-to=2014-10-13&amp;dept=29&amp;uin=208928" target="_blank">208928</a>.</p>","Thornbury and Yate","Steve Webb",,"2015-03-26T09:14:54.26Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/229263/answer","Biography information for Steve Webb","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/229263/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/229263/answer",,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2015-03-23","Children: Maintenance","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, what assessment he has made of the effect on child poverty of the introduction of child maintenance service charges.","false","Biography information for Mike Wood","Batley and Spen","Mike Wood","228852"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/229264","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2015-03-26","<p>Mandatory reconsideration is an entirely separate process to the new arrangements for dealing with Employment and Support Allowance (ESA) repeat claims. No change to the mandatory reconsideration process is required as a result. We keep the mandatory reconsideration process under review with the aim to improving the process as necessary.</p><p> </p><p>No estimate has been undertaken of the number of individuals previously entitled to claim ESA who will claim Jobseeker's Allowance (JSA) following the changes proposed by the ESA repeat claims project.</p><p> </p><p>The Department has made no specific estimate of the number of individuals previously entitled to ESA who would be entitled to JSA but choose not to claim it following the changes to the benefit rules.</p><p> </p><p>The Department does all that it can to encourage people found fit for work to claim JSA. ESA decision-makers make decision assurance calls which invite claimants to claim JSA where appropriate. Claimants are routed to the contact centre to discuss their claim with an agent. Where such calls are unsuccessful claimants are provided with a written notification of how to call the JSA contact centre to make a claim.</p>","Forest of Dean","Mr Mark Harper","228847 ; 228848 ; 228849","2015-03-26T08:46:17.727Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/229264/answer","Biography information for Mr Mark Harper","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/229264/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/229264/answer",,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2015-03-23","Employment and Support Allowance","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, what support will be provided to people no longer entitled to claim employment and support allowance following the changes proposed by the employment and support allowance repeat claims project who are eligible for but do not claim jobseeker's allowance.","false","Biography information for Ian Lavery","Wansbeck","Ian Lavery","228850"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/229265","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2015-03-26","<p>The information as requested is not readily available and could be provided only at disproportionate cost.</p>","Forest of Dean","Mr Mark Harper",,"2015-03-26T09:13:46.407Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/229265/answer","Biography information for Mr Mark Harper","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/229265/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/229265/answer",,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2015-03-23","Social Security Benefits: Medical Examinations","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, how many fit for work decisions were overturned on appeal in each month since October 2008.","false","Biography information for Ian Lavery","Wansbeck","Ian Lavery","228851"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/229266","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2015-03-26","<p>The assessment of the gender impact of fees and charges for the new Child Maintenance Service was published in the Equality Impact Assessment for the Child Support Fees Regulations 2013. This is available at: <a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/uploads/system/uploads/attachment_data/file/220219/eia-child-support-fees.pdf" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/uploads/system/uploads/attachment_data/file/220219/eia-child-support-fees.pdf</a>.</p>","Thornbury and Yate","Steve Webb",,"2015-03-26T09:20:32.353Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/229266/answer","Biography information for Steve Webb","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/229266/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/229266/answer",,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2015-03-23","Children: Maintenance","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, what assessment he has made of the gender impact of the introduction of child maintenance service charges.","false","Biography information for Mike Wood","Batley and Spen","Mike Wood","228853"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/229536","Department for Business, Innovation and Skills","false","2015-03-26","<p>The Skills Funding Agency does not allocate funding to specific geographical areas. The Agency allocates funding to colleges and training providers, some of whom provide training and skills services to learners and employers across the country.</p><p> </p><p>Adult Skills Budget Allocations have just been communicated to colleges and the total Budget for East Durham College in 2015/16 is £2,749,202. In 2014/15 it was £3,693,588.</p><p> </p>","Grantham and Stamford","Nick Boles",,"2015-03-26T14:28:12.043Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/229536/answer","Biography information for Nick Boles","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/229536/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/229536/answer",,,,,"26","Business, Innovation and Skills","Business, Innovation and Skills","2015-03-23","Adult Education: Durham","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Business, Innovation and Skills, what funding his Department has allocated for adult skills training in east Durham in 2015-16; and what amount was allocated for that purpose in 2014-15.","false","Biography information for Grahame Morris","Easington","Grahame M. Morris","908353"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/229537","Department for Business, Innovation and Skills","false","2015-03-26","<p><strong> </strong></p><p> </p><p>I have had no specific discussions with mobile phone operators on the issue of adverse weather, but there is a regular dialogue on issues of concern to both industry and Government.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p>The Department for Business, Innovation and Skills works closely with the telecoms industry, in particular via the pan industry and government Electronic Communications – Resilience &amp; Response Group (EC-RRG) which leads on enhancing resilience levels and the preparation and exercising of incident response.</p><p> </p>","Wantage","Mr Edward Vaizey",,"2015-03-26T14:30:15.543Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/229537/answer","Biography information for Mr Edward Vaizey","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/229537/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/229537/answer",,,,,"26","Business, Innovation and Skills","Business, Innovation and Skills","2015-03-23","Mobile Phones: Weather","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Business, Innovation and Skills, what discussions he has had with mobile phone operators on the effects of adverse weather on their systems; and if he will make a statement.","false","Biography information for Mr Charles Kennedy","Ross, Skye and Lochaber","Mr Charles Kennedy","908354"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/229538","Department for Business, Innovation and Skills","false","2015-03-26","<p>The European Single Market gives British firms access to 500 million consumers and, as our largest trading partner, is responsible for almost half of this country’s exports. A wide range of economic studies demonstrate the benefits to the UK economy from EU membership.</p><p> </p>","Twickenham","Vince Cable",,"2015-03-26T14:31:59.61Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/229538/answer","Biography information for Sir Vince Cable","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/229538/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/229538/answer",,,,,"26","Business, Innovation and Skills","Business, Innovation and Skills","2015-03-23","UK Membership of EU","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Business, Innovation and Skills, what recent assessment he has made of the contribution of EU membership to business and the economy in the UK.","false","Biography information for Bridget Phillipson","Houghton and Sunderland South","Bridget Phillipson","908352"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/229539","Department for Business, Innovation and Skills","false","2015-03-26","<p>We have taken unprecedented step to bring transparency to late payment, and I can tell the House I have written to all signatories to the Prompt Payment Code to set out the new requirements of a 30 day payment term as the norm, with a 60 day maximum. And we have legislated to require 30 day payment terms to be mandated down entire supply chains for public sector work.</p><p> </p>","West Suffolk","Matthew Hancock",,"2015-03-26T14:33:09.907Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/229539/answer","Biography information for Matt Hancock","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/229539/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/229539/answer",,,,,"26","Business, Innovation and Skills","Business, Innovation and Skills","2015-03-23","Small Businesses: Billing","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Business, Innovation and Skills, what steps he is taking to tackle late payment to small businesses.","false","Biography information for Dr Matthew Offord","Hendon","Dr Matthew Offord","908351"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/229540","Department for Business, Innovation and Skills","false","2015-03-26","<p>Since this Government was elected 1.9 million more people are in employment, with jobs created in every region of the country – 60% outside London and the South East.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p>The 28 City Deals, and 39 Local Growth Deals are helping drive local growth by transferring powers and resources from Whitehall to local economies.</p><p> </p>","Tunbridge Wells","Greg Clark",,"2015-03-26T14:22:13.97Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/229540/answer","Biography information for Greg Clark","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/229540/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/229540/answer",,,,,"26","Business, Innovation and Skills","Business, Innovation and Skills","2015-03-23","Regional Planning and Development","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Business, Innovation and Skills, what steps he is taking to promote regional growth.","false","Biography information for Mark Menzies","Fylde","Mark Menzies","908356"
