d Heritage Good Causes, net of Olympic transfers and operational costs. These are cash figures.)</p>","Maidstone and The Weald","Mrs Helen Grant",,"2015-03-26T09:29:23.47Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/228858/answer","Biography information for Mrs Helen Grant","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/228858/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/228858/answer",,,,,"10","Culture, Media and Sport","Culture, Media and Sport","2015-03-20","National Lottery","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Culture, Media and Sport, what funding has been allocated to (a) the arts, (b) sport and (c) heritage from the National Lottery in each of the last eight years for which figures are available; and what the aggregate equivalent figures are for (i) the arts, (ii) sport and (iii) heritage from (A) 2006 to 2010 and (B) 2010 to 2014.","false","Biography information for Chris Heaton-Harris","Daventry","Chris Heaton-Harris","228614"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/228859","Department for Culture Media and Sport","false","2015-03-26","<p>A. In 2010 the Government announced its intention to revert to the original funding allocations for Arts, Sports and Heritage Good Causes. This saw the proportions shift in two phases from 16.66% to 20% over 2011-2013.</p>","Maidstone and The Weald","Mrs Helen Grant",,"2015-03-26T09:27:18.337Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/228859/answer","Biography information for Mrs Helen Grant","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/228859/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/228859/answer",,,,,"10","Culture, Media and Sport","Culture, Media and Sport","2015-03-20","National Lottery","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Culture, Media and Sport, what changes to the proportion of National Lottery funding committed to (a) the arts, (b) sport and (c) heritage there have been in the last five years.","false","Biography information for Chris Heaton-Harris","Daventry","Chris Heaton-Harris","228613"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/228860","Department for Energy and Climate Change","false","2015-03-24","<p>The UK’s objectives for the 21<sup>st</sup> meeting of the Conference of the Parties (COP21) to the United Nations Framework Convention on Climate Change (UNFCCC) are to secure an ambitious and legally binding agreement that includes mitigation commitments from all countries to help reduce emissions globally, consistent with a path towards the 2°C goal. The UK also wants the Agreement to recognise the importance of, and encourage, support to those who need it, particularly the poorest and most vulnerable, to take climate action and develop climate resilience.</p>","Hastings and Rye","Amber Rudd",,"2015-03-24T16:53:38.923Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/228860/answer","Biography information for Amber Rudd","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/228860/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/228860/answer",,,,,"63","Energy and Climate Change","Energy and Climate Change","2015-03-20","Climate Change","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Energy and Climate Change, what the Government's objectives are for the December 2015 UN Climate Change Conference.","false","Biography information for Mr Nicholas Brown","Newcastle upon Tyne East","Mr Nicholas Brown","228601"
