"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/228479","Cabinet Office","false","2015-03-24","<p>The Prime Minister’s Office is an integral part of the Cabinet Office.</p><p>As was the case under the previous administration, officials are not compelled to declare their ethnicity. Statistically valid information about pay broken down by ethnicity is therefore not available</p><p>Diversity data on the declared ethnic background of Non-Executive Board Members and Government Board Members appointed since 2010 is not held centrally.</p><p>The Cabinet Office will shortly publish the report by Ethnic Dimension Research &amp; Consultancy on &quot;Identifying and Removing Barriers to Talented BAME Staff Progression in the Civil Service&quot; and an updated Talent Action Plan.</p><p> </p>","Horsham","Mr Francis Maude","228301 ; 228327 ; 228467 ; 228571","2015-03-24T16:37:04.24Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/228479/answer","Biography information for Lord Maude of Horsham","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/228479/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/228479/answer",,,,,"53","Cabinet Office","Cabinet Office","2015-03-19","Government Departments: Public Appointments","1","House of Commons","To ask the Minister for the Cabinet Office, what proportion of members of Government Boards identify as from Black, Asian or other minority ethnic groups.","false","Biography information for Gloria De Piero","Ashfield","Gloria De Piero","228466"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/228480","Cabinet Office","false","2015-03-24","<p>The Prime Minister’s Office is an integral part of the Cabinet Office.</p><p>As was the case under the previous administration, officials are not compelled to declare their ethnicity. Statistically valid information about pay broken down by ethnicity is therefore not available</p><p>Diversity data on the declared ethnic background of Non-Executive Board Members and Government Board Members appointed since 2010 is not held centrally.</p><p>The Cabinet Office will shortly publish the report by Ethnic Dimension Research &amp; Consultancy on &quot;Identifying and Removing Barriers to Talented BAME Staff Progression in the Civil Service&quot; and an updated Talent Action Plan.</p><p> </p>","Horsham","Mr Francis Maude","228301 ; 228327 ; 228466 ; 228571","2015-03-24T16:37:04.377Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/228480/answer","Biography information for Lord Maude of Horsham","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/228480/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/228480/answer",,,,,"53","Cabinet Office","Cabinet Office","2015-03-19","Government Departments: Public Appointments","1","House of Commons","To ask the Minister for the Cabinet Office, what proportion of Government appointments were made to people identified as from Black, Asian or other minority ethnic groups in each year from 2010 to date.","false","Biography information for Gloria De Piero","Ashfield","Gloria De Piero","228467"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/228481","Cabinet Office","false","2015-03-24","<p>The Prime Minister’s Office is an integral part of the Cabinet Office.</p><p>As was the case under the previous administration, officials are not compelled to declare their ethnicity. Statistically valid information about pay broken down by ethnicity is therefore not available</p><p>Diversity data on the declared ethnic background of Non-Executive Board Members and Government Board Members appointed since 2010 is not held centrally.</p><p>The Cabinet Office will shortly publish the report by Ethnic Dimension Research &amp; Consultancy on &quot;Identifying and Removing Barriers to Talented BAME Staff Progression in the Civil Service&quot; and an updated Talent Action Plan.</p><p> </p>","Horsham","Mr Francis Maude","228327 ; 228466 ; 228467 ; 228571","2015-03-24T16:37:04.1Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/228481/answer","Biography information for Lord Maude of Horsham","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/228481/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/228481/answer",,,,,"53","Cabinet Office","Cabinet Office","2015-03-19","Pay","1","House of Commons","To ask the Minister for the Cabinet Office, what the average hourly pay is of employees at each grade in the Prime Minister's Office identified as (a) White or White British and (b) from a black, Asian or other minority ethnic group.","false","Biography information for Gloria De Piero","Ashfield","Gloria De Piero","228301"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/228482","Cabinet Office","false","2015-03-24","<p>The department has made significant progress on the development of this Fund. The design of the Fund is being informed by the excellent feedback we received through the public consultation and wide-ranging sector engagement carried out in 2014.</p><p> </p><p> </p>","Reading East","Mr Rob Wilson",,"2015-03-24T16:18:35.947Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/228482/answer","Biography information for Mr Rob Wilson","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/228482/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/228482/answer",,,,,"53","Cabinet Office","Cabinet Office","2015-03-19","Third Sector: Finance","1","House of Commons","To ask the Minister for the Cabinet Office, what progress has been made on introducing the £40 million local sustainability fund for voluntary, community and social enterprise organisations.","false","Biography information for Lisa Nandy","Wigan","Lisa Nandy","228372"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/228483","Cabinet Office","false","2015-03-24","<p>The Prime Minister’s Office is an integral part of the Cabinet Office.</p><p>As was the case under the previous administration, officials are not compelled to declare their ethnicity. Statistically valid information about pay broken down by ethnicity is therefore not available</p><p>Diversity data on the declared ethnic background of Non-Executive Board Members and Government Board Members appointed since 2010 is not held centrally.</p><p>The Cabinet Office will shortly publish the report by Ethnic Dimension Research &amp; Consultancy on &quot;Identifying and Removing Barriers to Talented BAME Staff Progression in the Civil Service&quot; and an updated Talent Action Plan.</p><p> </p>","Horsham","Mr Francis Maude","228301 ; 228466 ; 228467 ; 228571","2015-03-24T16:37:03.973Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/228483/answer","Biography information for Lord Maude of Horsham","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/228483/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/228483/answer",,,,,"53","Cabinet Office","Cabinet Office","2015-03-19","Pay","1","House of Commons","To ask the Minister for the Cabinet Office, what the median hourly pay is for all employees in each ethnic group in his Department.","false","Biography information for Gloria De Piero","Ashfield","Gloria De Piero","228327"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/228484","Cabinet Office","false","2015-03-24","<p>The Civil Contingencies Act places the primary responsibility for emergency planning on local responders working together. This activity at local level is constantly developing in the light of testing and exercising and actual events. It is supported at the national level by a range of activities including the production of the National Risk Assessment (NRA), a classified biennial assessment that identifies and prioritises the most significant emergencies the UK could face over the next five years, with the 2014 NRA having recently been made available to local responders; the cross-government National Resilience Capability Programme supported by the 2014 National Capability Survey, a voluntary biennial survey of local responders which provides data to government and enables self-improvement activity at the local tier; and the doctrine and training provided by the Emergency Planning College. In addition, the government’s annual review of UK resilience continues to consider the local, regional, and national level issues that pose the greatest risks to the UK.</p><p> </p>","West Dorset","Mr Oliver Letwin",,"2015-03-24T15:26:40.647Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/228484/answer","Biography information for Sir Oliver Letwin","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/228484/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/228484/answer",,,,,"53","Cabinet Office","Cabinet Office","2015-03-19","Emergencies: Planning","1","House of Commons","To ask the Minister for the Cabinet Office, what recent progress he has made on civil contingencies planning.","false","Biography information for Baroness McIntosh of Pickering","Thirsk and Malton","Miss Anne McIntosh","228353"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/228485","HM Treasury","false","2015-03-26","<p>EU VAT law does not enable an exemption of VAT for the installation of high-speed broadband cabinets. However, the government has provided £1.7bn of direct funding to deliver superfast broadband to 95% of premises by 2017 with over 2 million homes reached so far. The broadband connection voucher scheme has also been extended to March 2016 and will be available in a total of 50 cities by 1 April 2015. The scheme provides vouchers of up to £3,000 to support broadband connection upgrades for small businesses, charities, social enterprises and sole traders.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p>At Budget we also announced a new ambition that ultrafast broadband of at least 100 Megabits per second should become available to nearly all UK premises, to be supported by market delivery and government action to remove barriers to investment and reduce red tape.</p><p> </p>","Witham","Priti Patel",,"2015-03-26T10:00:19.577Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/228485/answer","Biography information for Priti Patel","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/228485/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/228485/answer",,,,,"14","Treasury","Treasury","2015-03-19","Broadband: VAT","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, if he will make it his policy to exempt community groups, charities and other not-for-profit organisations from the requirement to pay VAT on the installation of government-funded high-speed broadband cabinets; and if he will make a statement.","false","Biography information for Sir Bob Russell","Colchester","Sir Bob Russell","228362"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/228486","HM Treasury","false","2015-03-24","<p>In line with the Ministerial Code, as the Chief Secretary to the Treasury I asked Treasury officials to calculate the impact on the fiscal aggregates of a set for alternative assumptions on tax and spend for the years beyond 2016-17. All costs were met from within existing budgets.</p><p> </p>","Inverness, Nairn, Badenoch and Strathspey","Danny Alexander","228371","2015-03-24T17:45:31.217Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/228486/answer","Biography information for Danny Alexander","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/228486/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/228486/answer",,,,,"14","Treasury","Treasury","2015-03-19","Fiscal Policy","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, what the (a) total and (b) staff cost to his Department was of producing the document, An alternative fiscal path beyond 2016-17, published on 19 March 2015.","false","Biography information for Mr Chris Leslie","Nottingham East","Chris Leslie","228370"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/228487","HM Treasury","false","2015-03-24","<p>In line with the Ministerial Code, as the Chief Secretary to the Treasury I asked Treasury officials to calculate the impact on the fiscal aggregates of a set for alternative assumptions on tax and spend for the years beyond 2016-17. All costs were met from within existing budgets.</p><p> </p>","Inverness, Nairn, Badenoch and Strathspey","Danny Alexander","228370","2015-03-24T17:45:31.413Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/228487/answer","Biography information for Danny Alexander","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/228487/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/228487/answer",,,,,"14","Treasury","Treasury","2015-03-19","Fiscal Policy","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, how many officials in his Department were involved in producing the document, An alternative fiscal path beyond 2016-17, published on 19 March 2015.","false","Biography information for Mr Chris Leslie","Nottingham East","Chris Leslie","228371"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/228488","Department for Transport","false","2015-03-24","<p>The department does not hold estimates of future freight container activity for individual ports, nor estimates of the mode used for onward journeys.</p>","South Holland and The Deepings","Mr John Hayes",,"2015-03-24T15:26:44.263Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/228488/answer","Biography information for Sir John Hayes","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/228488/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/228488/answer",,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2015-03-19","Ports: Freight","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, if he will make an estimate of the number of freight containers that will be moved from (a) Felixstowe and (b) Tilbury port by (i) rail and (ii) road in the next two years.","true","Biography information for Kelvin Hopkins","Luton North","Kelvin Hopkins","228413"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/228489","HM Treasury","false","2015-03-24","<p>HM Treasury has made no detailed estimate of the effect of the change in oil price since August 2014 specifically in relation to the cost of moving freight by rail, road or sea.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p>However Government have made clear that it expects industry to pass any savings that result from lower oil prices onto their customers.</p><p> </p>","Witham","Priti Patel",,"2015-03-24T16:59:45.23Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/228489/answer","Biography information for Priti Patel","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/228489/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/228489/answer",,,,,"14","Treasury","Treasury","2015-03-19","Transport: Freight","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, what estimate he has made of the effects of changes in oil prices since August 2014 on the cost of moving freight by (a) rail, (b) road and (c) sea.","true","Biography information for Kelvin Hopkins","Luton North","Kelvin Hopkins","228412"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/228490","HM Treasury","false","2015-03-25","<p>Supplies of residential property letting are exempt from VAT, so businesses that only make such exempt supplies are not entitled to register for VAT.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p>In each of the relevant years, the number of VAT- registered businesses whose declared trade classification was Letting or Renting own or Leased Real Estate was as follows:</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><table><tbody><tr><td><p> </p><p>Year</p></td><td><p> </p><p>No of VAT registered businesses</p></td></tr><tr><td><p> </p><p>2005</p></td><td><p>4,089</p></td></tr><tr><td><p> </p><p>2006</p></td><td><p>4,997</p></td></tr><tr><td><p> </p><p>2007</p></td><td><p>6,264</p></td></tr><tr><td><p> </p><p>2008</p></td><td><p>10,860</p></td></tr><tr><td><p> </p><p>2009</p></td><td><p>14,701</p></td></tr><tr><td><p> </p><p>2010</p></td><td><p> </p><p>18,774</p></td></tr><tr><td><p> </p><p>2011</p></td><td><p> </p><p>22,520</p></td></tr><tr><td><p> </p><p>2012</p></td><td><p> </p><p>26,076</p></td></tr><tr><td><p> </p><p>2013</p></td><td><p> </p><p>29,149</p></td></tr><tr><td><p> </p><p>2014</p></td><td><p> </p><p>32,502</p></td></tr></tbody></table><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p>","South Northamptonshire","Andrea Leadsom","227906","2015-03-25T17:47:41.71Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/228490/answer","Biography information for Andrea Leadsom","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/228490/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/228490/answer",,,,,"14","Treasury","Treasury","2015-03-19","VAT","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, how many VAT-registered property rental companies there were in each year since May 2010.","false","Biography information for Pamela Nash","Airdrie and Shotts","Pamela Nash","228302"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/228491","HM Treasury","false","2015-03-24","<p>The Government has received a number of representations from the ‘Cut Tourism VAT’ campaign.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p>I refer the Hon gentleman to my comments during the recent Westminster Hall debate on 17 March 2015.</p><p> </p><p> </p>","South West Hertfordshire","Mr David Gauke",,"2015-03-24T17:52:47.157Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/228491/answer","Biography information for Mr David Gauke","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/228491/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/228491/answer",,,,,"14","Treasury","Treasury","2015-03-19","VAT","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, what recent representations his Department has received on the level of VAT applicable to small tourist businesses.","false","Biography information for Mr Geoffrey Cox","Torridge and West Devon","Mr Geoffrey Cox","228304"
