"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/228493","HM Treasury","false","2015-03-24","<p>Where a dispute arises between HMRC and a customer in relation to their tax affairs, HMRC will only resolve the dispute in a way that secures the tax that is due under the current law. HMRC’s Litigation &amp; Settlement Strategy (LSS) – which applies to all tax disputes - sets out its approach to securing the tax due as efficiently as possible and in accordance with the law. The governance procedures for how HMRC settles disputes are set out in the published Code of Governance for resolving tax disputes. Together the LSS and the Code of Governance assure taxpayers that tax rules are applied appropriately and even-handedly by HMRC.</p><p> </p>","South West Hertfordshire","Mr David Gauke",,"2015-03-24T17:54:40.767Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/228493/answer","Biography information for Mr David Gauke","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/228493/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/228493/answer",,,,,"14","Treasury","Treasury","2015-03-19","Football: Taxation","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, whether HM Revenue and Customs has made special arrangements with English Premier League clubs about their tax affairs.","false","Biography information for Mr Mike Hancock","Portsmouth South","Mr Mike Hancock","228454"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/228494","HM Treasury","false","2015-03-24","<p>HM Revenue &amp; Customs has made no estimate of the number of car wash businesses in the UK or the tax paid by such businesses in the last year because information is not available at that level of disaggregation.</p><p> </p>","South West Hertfordshire","Mr David Gauke",,"2015-03-24T17:56:16.63Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/228494/answer","Biography information for Mr David Gauke","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/228494/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/228494/answer",,,,,"14","Treasury","Treasury","2015-03-19","Car Washes","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, what estimate he has made of the number of car wash businesses in the UK; and what estimate he has made of the tax paid by such businesses in the last year.","false","Biography information for Philip Davies","Shipley","Philip Davies","228455"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/228495","HM Treasury","false","2015-03-24","<p>The Treasury Ministers and officials discuss a variety of issues with a range of industry stakeholders throughout the year, including between the dates outlined in the question.</p><p> </p>","Witham","Priti Patel",,"2015-03-24T17:00:32.913Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/228495/answer","Biography information for Priti Patel","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/228495/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/228495/answer",,,,,"14","Treasury","Treasury","2015-03-19","Alcoholic Drinks: Excise Duties","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, what meetings (a) Ministers and (b) officials in his Department had on alcohol duty with representatives of (i) the Wine and Spirits Trade Association, (ii) the Scotch Whisky Association, (iii) the British Beer and Pub Association, (iv) Diageo, (v) SAB Miller and (vi) the Portman Group between 1 November 2014 and 18 March 2015.","false","Biography information for Kelvin Hopkins","Luton North","Kelvin Hopkins","228414"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/228496","HM Treasury","false","2015-03-26","<p>HMRC have a statutory duty of confidentiality which limits the information they can disclose, including to Ministers. However, I can refer the Honourable Member to the answer given on 18<sup>th</sup> July 2014 in HL1269, which was based on the company’s accounts.</p><p> </p>","Witham","Priti Patel",,"2015-03-26T09:55:07.237Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/228496/answer","Biography information for Priti Patel","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/228496/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/228496/answer",,,,,"14","Treasury","Treasury","2015-03-19","Severn River Crossing","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, how much in VAT revenue accrued to the public purse from the Severn Crossings tolls in (a) 2013-14 and (b) 2012-13.","false","Biography information for Jessica Morden","Newport East","Jessica Morden","228410"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/228497","HM Treasury","false","2015-03-24","<p>HMRC is not able to give this level of information as it breaches taxpayer confidentiality.</p><p> </p>","South West Hertfordshire","Mr David Gauke",,"2015-03-24T17:55:28.353Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/228497/answer","Biography information for Mr David Gauke","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/228497/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/228497/answer",,,,,"14","Treasury","Treasury","2015-03-19","Severn River Crossing","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, how much additional revenue accrued to the public purse from the Severn Crossings as a result of the abolition of the Industrial Buildings Allowance in (a) 2013-14, (b) 2012-13 and (c) 2011-12.","false","Biography information for Jessica Morden","Newport East","Jessica Morden","228411"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/228498","HM Treasury","false","2015-03-26","<p>Policies are assessed according to the Green Book principles, which take account of environmental impact.</p><p> </p>","Witham","Priti Patel",,"2015-03-26T09:58:02.457Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/228498/answer","Biography information for Priti Patel","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/228498/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/228498/answer",,,,,"14","Treasury","Treasury","2015-03-19","Budget March 2015","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, if he will publish an (a) environmental impact and (b) environmental sustainability assessment of Budget 2015, HC 1093.","false","Biography information for Paul Flynn","Newport West","Paul Flynn","228439"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/228499","HM Treasury","false","2015-03-24","<p>The Treasury Ministers and officials discuss a variety of issues with a range of industry stakeholders throughout the year, including between the dates outlined in the question.</p><p> </p>","Witham","Priti Patel",,"2015-03-24T17:01:53.38Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/228499/answer","Biography information for Priti Patel","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/228499/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/228499/answer",,,,,"14","Treasury","Treasury","2015-03-19","Alcoholic Drinks: Excise Duties","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, what meetings Ministers and officials in his Department had with alcohol companies and their representative organisations on alcohol duty between 1 November 2014 and 18 March 2015.","false","Biography information for Alex Cunningham","Stockton North","Alex Cunningham","228429"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/228500","HM Treasury","false","2015-03-25","<p>This work will be undertaken from within existing budgets at the Cabinet Office. The Government will engage as the sector draws up plans to help take advantage of the opportunities the new digital age presents – protecting frontline services whilst delivering efficiencies. If the sector is able to deliver these proposals, they could contribute towards our goal, as announced at Autumn Statement 14, of a further £10bn efficiency savings.</p><p> </p>","Inverness, Nairn, Badenoch and Strathspey","Danny Alexander",,"2015-03-25T15:58:20.213Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/228500/answer","Biography information for Danny Alexander","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/228500/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/228500/answer",,,,,"14","Treasury","Treasury","2015-03-19","Electronic Government","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, whether he will provide additional funding to enable Government Digital Service (GDS) to work with local government on digital services; to which bodies that will be allocated; and whether he expects GDS to grow in size.","false","Biography information for Chi Onwurah","Newcastle upon Tyne Central","Chi Onwurah","228497"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/228501","Department for Business, Innovation and Skills","false","2015-03-26","<p>The Collaboratorium for Research in Infrastructure and Cities consortium is identifying potential industrial and institutional co-investors as part of the business case development for this initiative. Government is ready to support leveraged funding where appropriate.</p><p> </p>","Tunbridge Wells","Greg Clark",,"2015-03-26T14:35:53.077Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/228501/answer","Biography information for Greg Clark","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/228501/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/228501/answer",,,,,"26","Business, Innovation and Skills","Business, Innovation and Skills","2015-03-19","Infrastructure","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Business, Innovation and Skills, with reference to paragraph 1.185 of Budget 2015, which bodies he expects to provide co-funding for the Collaboratorium for Research in Infrastructure and Cities; and what steps he is taking to encourage such co-funding.","false","Biography information for Chi Onwurah","Newcastle upon Tyne Central","Chi Onwurah","228495"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/228502","HM Treasury","false","2015-03-26","<p>This question can be answered using publically available information at the following links;</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p>Letter from the Finance Director for the Department of Culture Media and Sport to the CEO of Arts Council England on 26 March 2014.</p><p> </p><p><strong><a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/uploads/system/uploads/attachment_data/file/310064/ACE_Revised_Allocation_Letter_2013_14_-_2015_16.pdf" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/uploads/system/uploads/attachment_data/file/310064/ACE_Revised_Allocation_Letter_2013_14_-_2015_16.pdf</a></strong></p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p>GDP deflators at market prices, and money GDP.</p><p> </p><p><strong><a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/statistics/gdp-deflators-at-market-prices-and-money-gdp-march-2015-budget-2015" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/statistics/gdp-deflators-at-market-prices-and-money-gdp-march-2015-budget-2015</a></strong></p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p>","Inverness, Nairn, Badenoch and Strathspey","Danny Alexander",,"2015-03-26T10:17:19.697Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/228502/answer","Biography information for Danny Alexander","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/228502/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/228502/answer",,,,,"14","Treasury","Treasury","2015-03-19","Arts Council England","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, what the real terms change in Grant in Aid for the Arts Council (England) will be from 2014-15 to 2015-16 using the Office for Budget Responsibility forecast for the GDP deflator; and when the Arts Council (England) was informed of that change.","false","Biography information for Chris Bryant","Rhondda","Chris Bryant","228507"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/228503","HM Treasury","false","2015-03-23","<p>In the specified Budget 2015 paragraph references, “available to” means that consumers should be able to access ultrafast broadband through a retail service, should they choose to take one up.</p><p> </p>","Inverness, Nairn, Badenoch and Strathspey","Danny Alexander",,"2015-03-23T16:04:51.173Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/228503/answer","Biography information for Danny Alexander","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/228503/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/228503/answer",,,,,"14","Treasury","Treasury","2015-03-19","Broadband","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, with reference to paragraphs 1.103, 1.122 and 2.231 of Budget 2015, on the availability of ultrafast broadband, what the Government's definition is of "available to".","false","Biography information for Chi Onwurah","Newcastle upon Tyne Central","Chi Onwurah","228477"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/228504","HM Treasury","false","2015-03-24","<p>HM Revenue &amp; Customs intends to provide all of its customers with their own personalised digital tax account. To what extent a person chooses to use their digital tax account will be an individual choice.</p><p> </p>","South West Hertfordshire","Mr David Gauke",,"2015-03-24T17:53:44.803Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/228504/answer","Biography information for Mr David Gauke","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/228504/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/228504/answer",,,,,"14","Treasury","Treasury","2015-03-19","Taxation: Self-assessment","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, with reference to paragraph 1.108 of Budget 2015, whether people will be able to opt out of the digital tax accounts.","false","Biography information for Chi Onwurah","Newcastle upon Tyne Central","Chi Onwurah","228496"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/228505","Department for Communities and Local Government","false","2015-03-26","<p>The information requested is shown in the attached table.<br><br>Averages and headcount figures have been calculated against staff included in the Department headcount under the Office of National Statistics definition as of 28 February 2015. This includes all staff paid via the Department’s payroll and employed on either a permanent, fixed term or interchange basis.</p><p> </p><p>Department employees that did not provide or consent to the disclosure of their diversity information have not been included in the staff numbers or salary averages.</p><p> </p><p>Until recent reform staff below the Senior Civil Service in DCLG had contractual pay progression, this linked increases in pay to length of service and it is this factor that is likely to underpin any differences in hourly rate, length of service, rather than ethnicity itself is the causal factor.<br><br></p>","Keighley","Kris Hopkins",,"2015-03-26T14:01:39.567Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/228505/answer","Biography information for Kris Hopkins","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/228505/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/228505/answer",,,,,"7","Communities and Local Government","Communities and Local Government","2015-03-19","Pay","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Communities and Local Government, what the average hourly pay is of employees at each grade within his Department identified as (a) White or White British and (b) from a Black, Asian or other minority ethnic group.","false","Biography information for Gloria De Piero","Ashfield","Gloria De Piero","228306"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/228506","Department for Communities and Local Government","false","2015-03-23","<p>The levels of household waste sent for reuse, recycling or composting in a) Pendle Borough Council and b) Lancashire County Council in those years is set out in the table below:<br><br></p><table><tbody><tr><td> </td><td>2009/10</td><td>2010/11</td><td>2011/12</td><td>2012/13</td><td>2013/14</td></tr><tr><td>Pendle</td><td>35.6%</td><td>38.0%</td><td>37.6%</td><td>35.9%</td><td>36.7%</td></tr><tr><td>Lancashire</td><td>44.9%</td><td>46.0%</td><td>46.8%</td><td>47.6%</td><td>47.4%</td></tr></tbody></table><p> </p><p> </p>","Keighley","Kris Hopkins",,"2015-03-23T14:38:49.293Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/228506/answer","Biography information for Kris Hopkins","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/228506/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/228506/answer",,,,,"7","Communities and Local Government","Communities and Local Government","2015-03-19","Recycling: Lancashire","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Communities and Local Government, how much waste was recycled in (a) Pendle constituency and (b) Lancashire in 2009-10 and each subsequent year.","false","Biography information for Andrew Stephenson","Pendle","Andrew Stephenson","228349"
