"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/228508","Department for Culture Media and Sport","false","2015-03-24","<p>The Government's broadband initiatives to expand broadband coverage in rural areas and improve business connectivity in cities provides opportunities for internet service providers to compete and the market to grow.</p><p> </p>","Wantage","Mr Edward Vaizey",,"2015-03-24T13:44:28.787Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/228508/answer","Biography information for Mr Edward Vaizey","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/228508/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/228508/answer",,,,,"10","Culture, Media and Sport","Culture, Media and Sport","2015-03-19","Internet","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Culture, Media and Sport, what steps he has taken to support internet service providers and ensure they remain a facilitator for the online industry.","false","Biography information for Mike Weatherley","Hove","Mike Weatherley","228399"
