"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/228510","Department for Culture Media and Sport","false","2015-03-25","<p>Sincethe DCMS hosted the future of local newspapers summit in November 2014, Department officials have been engaging regularly with a wide range of stakeholders to discuss the future of the industry.As part of Budget this Government announced that it will consult on whether to introduce a business rates relief for all local newspapers in England to help them adapt to new technology and changing circumstances.</p>","Wantage","Mr Edward Vaizey",,"2015-03-25T17:43:28.707Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/228510/answer","Biography information for Mr Edward Vaizey","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/228510/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/228510/answer",,,,,"10","Culture, Media and Sport","Culture, Media and Sport","2015-03-19","Local Press","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Culture, Media and Sport, what steps he is taking to safeguard the future of local newspapers.","false","Biography information for Frank Field","Birkenhead","Mr Frank Field","228476"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/228511","Department for Culture Media and Sport","false","2015-03-24","<p>The Department has not carried out specific research into people from lower income families employed in the acting or singing professions, however, the Qualification Blueprint research commissioned by Creative and Cultural Skills in 2011 goes into some detail on the educational background of people who work in the industries specified:<a href="http://blueprintfiles.s3.amazonaws.com/1319716392-Qualifications-Blueprint.pdf" target="_blank">http://blueprintfiles.s3.amazonaws.com/1319716392-Qualifications-Blueprint.pdf</a></p>","Wantage","Mr Edward Vaizey",,"2015-03-24T13:45:18.16Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/228511/answer","Biography information for Mr Edward Vaizey","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/228511/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/228511/answer",,,,,"10","Culture, Media and Sport","Culture, Media and Sport","2015-03-19","Arts: Employment","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Culture, Media and Sport, what estimate he has made of the number of people employed in the (a) acting and (b) singing professions from lower income families in each year since May 2010.","false","Biography information for Dan Jarvis","Barnsley Central","Dan Jarvis","228484"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/228512","Department for Culture Media and Sport","false","2015-03-24","<p>The Government has not received any representations from internet service providers on the exemption from liabilities (&quot;safe harbour&quot;) provisions contained within the eCommerce Directive. Some rights holders have expressed concern that the exemption from liabilities provisions are no longer necessary in their current form. The UK government recently published its vision for the future of the digital economy in the EU, and we will continue to seek the views of all stakeholders in developing our policy in this area.</p>","Wantage","Mr Edward Vaizey","228460","2015-03-24T13:40:17.307Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/228512/answer","Biography information for Mr Edward Vaizey","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/228512/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/228512/answer",,,,,"10","Culture, Media and Sport","Culture, Media and Sport","2015-03-19","Internet Service Providers","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Culture, Media and Sport, what representations his Department has received from internet service providers on safe harbour provisions.","false","Biography information for Mike Weatherley","Hove","Mike Weatherley","228459"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/228513","Department for Culture Media and Sport","false","2015-03-24","<p>The Government has not received any representations from internet service providers on the exemption from liabilities (&quot;safe harbour&quot;) provisions contained within the eCommerce Directive. Some rights holders have expressed concern that the exemption from liabilities provisions are no longer necessary in their current form. The UK government recently published its vision for the future of the digital economy in the EU, and we will continue to seek the views of all stakeholders in developing our policy in this area.</p>","Wantage","Mr Edward Vaizey","228459","2015-03-24T13:40:17.433Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/228513/answer","Biography information for Mr Edward Vaizey","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/228513/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/228513/answer",,,,,"10","Culture, Media and Sport","Culture, Media and Sport","2015-03-19","Internet Service Providers","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Culture, Media and Sport, what recent representations his Department has received from rights holders on safe harbour provisions.","false","Biography information for Mike Weatherley","Hove","Mike Weatherley","228460"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/228514","Ministry of Defence","false","2015-03-24","<p>Statistics showing enlistment into the Reserves are published by Defence Statistics in the Quarterly Personnel Report. The latest such report was published in February 2015.</p><p>https://www.gov.uk/government/statistics/uk-armed-forces-quarterly-personnel-report-2015</p><p>For ease of reference I am attaching the relevant page from this report.</p><p>The trained strength of the Army Reserve has risen by 560 in the past 12 months to 20,480, this is above our target for the year end of 19, 900.</p><p>I am confident that the plans of the Chief of the General Staff will be achieved.</p><p> </p>","Canterbury","Mr Julian Brazier",,"2015-03-24T17:16:47.797Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/228514/answer","Biography information for Sir Julian Brazier","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/228514/answer","Table 9a(1).xls HOC 228492.xls","Table 9a(1).xls HOC 228492.xls","Table 9a.xls","Table 9a.xls","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/228514/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2015-03-19","Army Reserve","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, what recent assessment he has made of the progress on recruitment of Army reservists  against his Department's target of 30,000 by 2019.","false","Biography information for Derek Twigg","Halton","Derek Twigg","228492"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/228515","Ministry of Defence","false","2015-03-26","<p>It has not proved possible to respond to the hon. Member in the time available before Prorogation.</p>","Broxtowe","Anna Soubry",,"2015-03-26T14:23:18.217Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/228515/answer","Biography information for Anna Soubry","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/228515/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/228515/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2015-03-19","Armed Forces: Official Residences","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, pursuant to the Answer of 7 August 2014 to Question 205237, what the cost to the public purse was of running and maintaining each residence formerly referred to as an official service residence provided by his Department to senior figures from the armed forces in 2012-13.","false","Biography information for Mr Kevan Jones","North Durham","Mr Kevan Jones","228445"
