"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/228525","Ministry of Defence","false","2015-03-25","<p>It has not proved possible to respond to the hon. Member in the time available before Prorogation.</p>","Broxtowe","Anna Soubry",,"2015-03-25T14:18:26.87Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/228525/answer","Biography information for Anna Soubry","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/228525/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/228525/answer","Broxtowe","Anna Soubry","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/228525/answer/previousversion/52561","Biography information for Anna Soubry","11","Defence","Defence","2015-03-19","Languages","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, how many (a) military and (b) civilian staff in his Department are proficient in (i) Arabic, (ii) Persian, (iii) Turkish, (iv) Berber, (v) Kurdish, (vi) Polish and (vii) Russian.","false","Biography information for Ian C. Lucas","Wrexham","Ian Lucas","228367"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/228526","Deputy Prime Minister","false","2015-03-26","<p>My officials, ministers and I​ maintain regular contact with the devolved administrations on matters of mutual interest, including constitutional reform​. Details of such exchanges are not usually published.</p><p> </p>","Sheffield, Hallam","Mr Nick Clegg",,"2015-03-26T09:24:28.973Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/228526/answer","Biography information for Mr Nick Clegg","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/228526/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/228526/answer",,,,,"58","Deputy Prime Minister","Deputy Prime Minister","2015-03-19","British Constitution","1","House of Commons","To ask the Deputy Prime Minister, what recent discussions he has had with the (a) First Minister of Scotland and (b) Secretary of State for Scotland on the Government's agenda for constitutional reform; and if he will make a statement.","false","Biography information for Baroness McIntosh of Pickering","Thirsk and Malton","Miss Anne McIntosh","228352"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/228527","Department for Education","false","2015-03-26","<p>Of the 45 Ofsted inspection reports of local authority children’s social care published under the single inspection framework, our records show that five reports refer to weaknesses in the timeliness of visits to children who are privately fostered. The Department for Education has introduced formal intervention measures for four of the five authorities in order to improve their performance across a range of areas.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p>Individual local authority Ofsted reports can be found at this link: <a href="http://reports.ofsted.gov.uk/" target="_blank">http://reports.ofsted.gov.uk/</a></p><p> </p>","Crewe and Nantwich","Mr Edward Timpson",,"2015-03-26T09:58:59.017Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/228527/answer","Biography information for Edward Timpson","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/228527/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/228527/answer",,,,,"60","Education","Education","2015-03-19","Foster Care","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Education, pursuant to the Answer of 29 January 2015 to Question 221699, on which occasions Ofsted has officially reported to her Department instances where a local authority had not complied with the statutory responsibility of six-week visits for privately fostered children.","false","Biography information for Steve McCabe","Birmingham, Selly Oak","Steve McCabe","228386"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/228528","Department for Education","false","2015-03-24","<p>The new School Food Standards came into force in January 2015 ensuring schools provide heathy meals throughout the week. The Department for Education provides guidance on the standards[1] and funds the implementation support service, including a menu checker service helping schools to provide hot, healthy menu choices for all their pupils. The School Food Plan website also provides a range of support and advice on providing healthy food in schools.[2]</p><p> </p><p> </p><p>[1] <a href="http://www.gov.uk/school-meals-healthy-eating-standards" target="_blank">www.gov.uk/school-meals-healthy-eating-standards</a></p><p>[2] <a href="http://whatworkswell.schoolfoodplan.com/" target="_blank">http://whatworkswell.schoolfoodplan.com/</a></p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p>","Yeovil","Mr David Laws",,"2015-03-24T14:04:50.95Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/228528/answer","Biography information for Mr David Laws","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/228528/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/228528/answer",,,,,"60","Education","Education","2015-03-19","Primary Education: Free School Meals","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Education, pursuant to the Answer of 12 March 2015 to Question 226581, what support her Department provides to primary schools to ensure that the free school meals offered by those schools are healthy.","false","Biography information for Nick de Bois","Enfield North","Nick de Bois","228392"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/228529","Department for Education","false","2015-03-24","<p>The Department for Education does not hold the information requested.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p>Information on the number of children looked after who are aged 12 years and over, and who are mothers, is published in Table A5 of the statistical first release ‘Children looked after in England including adoption’: <a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/statistics/children-looked-after-in-england-including-adoption--2" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/statistics/children-looked-after-in-england-including-adoption--2</a>.</p><p> </p>","Crewe and Nantwich","Mr Edward Timpson",,"2015-03-24T14:32:45.073Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/228529/answer","Biography information for Edward Timpson","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/228529/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/228529/answer",,,,,"60","Education","Education","2015-03-19","Children in Care","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Education, pursuant to the Answer of 29 January 2015 to Question 221701, how many teenage mothers became pregnant while in residential care in each year since 2010.","false","Biography information for Steve McCabe","Birmingham, Selly Oak","Steve McCabe","228387"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/228530","Department for Education","false","2015-03-24","<p>The Department for Education does not collect this information.</p><p> </p>","Crewe and Nantwich","Mr Edward Timpson",,"2015-03-24T14:31:39.587Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/228530/answer","Biography information for Edward Timpson","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/228530/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/228530/answer",,,,,"60","Education","Education","2015-03-19","Drugs: Young People","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Education, pursuant to the Answer of 2 February 2015 to Question 222185, how many times a court has overruled a young person's decision to refuse treatment for substance abuse.","false","Biography information for Steve McCabe","Birmingham, Selly Oak","Steve McCabe","228388"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/228531","Department for Education","false","2015-03-24","<p>Local authorities do not have any statutory obligation to notify the Department for Education when a child in the care of a local authority becomes pregnant.</p><p> </p>","Crewe and Nantwich","Mr Edward Timpson",,"2015-03-24T14:30:47.157Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/228531/answer","Biography information for Edward Timpson","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/228531/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/228531/answer",,,,,"60","Education","Education","2015-03-19","Children in Care","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Education, pursuant to the Answer of 29 January 2015 to Question 221702, whether local authorities have a statutory obligation to notify her Department when a child in their care becomes pregnant.","false","Biography information for Steve McCabe","Birmingham, Selly Oak","Steve McCabe","228389"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/228532","Department for Education","false","2015-03-24","<p>Supporting the teaching profession and reducing unnecessary workload which can lead to stress is an absolute priority for the Department for Education. Our response to the Workload Challenge[1] set out a comprehensive programme of action to be taken at every level in the school system, and the department will continue to do everything it can to relieve unnecessary burdens on teaching professionals.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p>School employers are responsible for the health of their workforce. It is vital that they have systems in place that identify and tackle the cause of stress in their staff and provide appropriate support for them. Headteachers also have a duty to promote the safety and wellbeing of staff and to lead and manage staff with a proper regard for their wellbeing. This includes the expectation of a healthy balance between work and other commitments outside the school.</p><p> </p><p>[1] <a href="http://www.gov.uk/government/publications/workload-challenge-for-schools-government-response" target="_blank">www.gov.uk/government/publications/workload-challenge-for-schools-government-response</a></p><p> </p>","Yeovil","Mr David Laws",,"2015-03-24T14:02:50.523Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/228532/answer","Biography information for Mr David Laws","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/228532/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/228532/answer",,,,,"60","Education","Education","2015-03-19","Teachers: Stress","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Education, what support her Department provides to teaching professionals affected by work-related stress.","false","Biography information for Dan Jarvis","Barnsley Central","Dan Jarvis","228486"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/228533","Department for Education","false","2015-03-24","<p>The information requested is not collected centrally.</p><p> </p>","Yeovil","Mr David Laws",,"2015-03-24T14:01:24.357Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/228533/answer","Biography information for Mr David Laws","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/228533/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/228533/answer",,,,,"60","Education","Education","2015-03-19","Teachers: Stress","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Education, what estimate she has made of the number of teachers who have taken leave from work because of stress in each year since May 2010.","false","Biography information for Dan Jarvis","Barnsley Central","Dan Jarvis","228487"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/228534","Department for Education","false","2015-03-24","<p>To publish now the names of schools which applied for but were not allocated funding would be unfair to the local authorities and schools which are affected by the announcement. Those organisations will be considering the next steps for resolving their situations; these might involve finding alternative capital funding sources or non-capital solutions. Publishing the details now could lead to unwelcome pressure from potential suppliers whilst they are considering their options. It is reasonable to assume that all authorities and schools will have decided on the approach they will be taking forward by July.</p><p> </p>","Yeovil","Mr David Laws",,"2015-03-24T14:03:33.56Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/228534/answer","Biography information for Mr David Laws","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/228534/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/228534/answer",,,,,"60","Education","Education","2015-03-19","Free School Meals","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Education, pursuant to the Answer of 16 March 2015 to Question 227136, for what reasons the names of schools which applied for but were not allocated funding will not be published until July 2015.","false","Biography information for Richard Burden","Birmingham, Northfield","Richard Burden","228428"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/228535","Department for Energy and Climate Change","false","2015-03-24","<p>National Grid expects the market to provide enough generation to meet demand and maintain system stability in Scotland – even if one or more major fossil fuelled plant closes. The system operator and transmission owners in Scotland (National Grid, Scottish Power Transmission and Scottish Hydro Electric Transmission) have stress tested scenarios in which Longannet and other Scottish fossil fuelled generators closed. National Grid has the tools to secure supplies under even the toughest system conditions, and the network is resilient against 1 in 600 year risks.</p><p>National Grid has published the advice that it provided to the Secretary of State and the Scottish government on this issue on their website this week. This information contains a description of the scenarios that have been tested, ‘A day in the life’ which shows that Scottish demand was secure on a low wind, high demand day, even if two large fossil fuelled power stations had not been available and an open letter providing reassurance on the status of electricity supply in Scotland:</p><p><a href="http://www2.nationalgrid.com/UK/Services/Balancing-services/System-security/Transmission-Constraint-Management/Transmission-Constraint-Management-Information/" target="_blank">http://www2.nationalgrid.com/UK/Services/Balancing-services/System-security/Transmission-Constraint-Management/Transmission-Constraint-Management-Information/</a>.</p>","West Suffolk","Matthew Hancock",,"2015-03-24T15:55:32.917Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/228535/answer","Biography information for Matt Hancock","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/228535/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/228535/answer",,,,,"63","Energy and Climate Change","Energy and Climate Change","2015-03-19","Longannet Power Station","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Energy and Climate Change, pursuant to the oral Answer of 19 March 2015 from the Minister of State for Energy, when he plans to publish the advice he has received on the effect on security of supply of the potential closure of Longannet.","false","Biography information for Tom Greatrex","Rutherglen and Hamilton West","Tom Greatrex","228508"
