"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/228614","Home Office","false","2015-03-24","<p>Numbers of staff in Her Majesty’s Passport Office processing passport applications as opposed to other duties are not classified under a single category. This information is therefore not held centrally and could only be obtained at disproportionate cost.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p>","Old Bexley and Sidcup","James Brokenshire",,"2015-03-24T15:29:36.34Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/228614/answer","Biography information for James Brokenshire","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/228614/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/228614/answer",,,,,"1","Home Office","Home Office","2015-03-19","Passports","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for the Home Department, how many staff were employed by her Department to process passport applications of any kind in each year since 2010.","false","Biography information for Steve McCabe","Birmingham, Selly Oak","Steve McCabe","228342"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/228615","Home Office","false","2015-03-24","<p>While the Home Office provides the majority of Government funding to the police, decisions on how this is spent are made locally by Police and Crime Commissioners (PCCs) and their chief constables. As such, the allocation of budgets by individual police forces in England and Wales to cover any potential additional costs arising from policing any events is entirely a local decision. This information is not collected centrally.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p>","Hemel Hempstead","Mike Penning",,"2015-03-24T15:25:52.137Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/228615/answer","Biography information for Sir Mike Penning","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/228615/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/228615/answer",,,,,"1","Home Office","Home Office","2015-03-19","Police: Football","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for the Home Department, how much each police force in the North West charged to each football club in their area for policing of football matches in 2014; and how much of those charges are currently outstanding.","false","Biography information for Sir Mark Hendrick","Preston","Mark Hendrick","228373"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/228616","Home Office","false","2015-03-24","<p>We are currently reviewing the information we provide to women asylum applicants at the point of claim to ensure that they are aware of the external services available to them and of their rights in the asylum process, such as the right to request an interviewer and interpreter of a particular gender. In conjunction with the United Nations High Commissioner for Refugees, the Refugee Council and the Scottish Refugee Council, we will shortly begin a pilot to signpost women who may have been the victims of sexual violence to existing support services.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p>","Old Bexley and Sidcup","James Brokenshire",,"2015-03-24T15:31:15.41Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/228616/answer","Biography information for James Brokenshire","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/228616/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/228616/answer",,,,,"1","Home Office","Home Office","2015-03-19","Asylum: Females","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for the Home Department, what steps she is taking to ensure that women are informed about all of their specific rights and entitlements within the asylum process.","false","Biography information for Toby Perkins","Chesterfield","Toby Perkins","228305"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/228617","Home Office","false","2015-03-26","<p>Table 1 shows the average hourly pay of civil servants in the Home Office as of 28th February 2015 by ethnicity.<br><br>Other than at Senior Civil Servant (SCS) level the Home Office have different pay scales for London and National at all grades. 78.2 % of the staff below SCS declaring themselves Black and Minority Ethnic are based in London compared with 33.2 % of staff below SCS declaring themselves White. This explains why (apart from SCS staff) the hourly rate for BME staff is higher than for white staff.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p>","Staffordshire Moorlands","Karen Bradley",,"2015-03-26T10:18:34.27Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/228617/answer","Biography information for Karen Bradley","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/228617/answer","PQ 228313 _Table 1.xlsx","PQ 228313 _Table 1.xlsx","Average hourly pay of civil servants","Average hourly pay of civil servants","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/228617/answer",,,,,"1","Home Office","Home Office","2015-03-19","Pay","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for the Home Department, what the average hourly pay is of employees at each grade within her Department identified as (a) White or White British and (b) from a Black, Asian or other minority ethnic group.","false","Biography information for Gloria De Piero","Ashfield","Gloria De Piero","228313"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/228618","House of Commons Commission","false","2015-03-24","<p>The minimum value for contracts that must be put out to competitive tender is £50,000. The contract was awarded under a Crown Commercial Service framework. In order to be part of the framework the suppliers have taken part in a competitive tender process.</p><p> </p>","Caithness, Sutherland and Easter Ross","John Thurso",,"2015-03-24T17:11:23.15Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/228618/answer","Biography information for Viscount Thurso","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/228618/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/228618/answer",,,,,"18","House of Commons Commission","House of Commons Commission","2015-03-19","ICT","1","House of Commons","To ask the hon. Member for Caithness, Sutherland and Easter Ross representing the House of Commons Commission, pursuant to the Answer of 18 March 2015 to Question 227500, what consideration was given to putting the contract for the supply of tablets for hon. Members out to competitive tender; and what the minimum value is for contracts that must be put out to competitive tender.","false","Biography information for Chi Onwurah","Newcastle upon Tyne Central","Chi Onwurah","228502"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/228619","House of Commons Commission","false","2015-03-24","<p>Following the election, each Member will be offered an iPad to facilitate use of online services provided by Parliament. These iPads, and the associated mobile data costs, will be funded from the Administration Estimate.</p><p>Members will also be able to order IT equipment from an online catalogue, financed from the Members Estimate. The catalogue will include a range of laptops, desktops, tablets, printers and peripherals to equip their offices. Parliamentary ICT (PICT) intends to offer devices in this catalogue that run the following operating systems, subject to security assurance and testing: Windows, iOS, OS X Yosemite and Android.</p>","Caithness, Sutherland and Easter Ross","John Thurso",,"2015-03-24T17:11:05.747Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/228619/answer","Biography information for Viscount Thurso","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/228619/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/228619/answer",,,,,"18","House of Commons Commission","House of Commons Commission","2015-03-19","ICT","1","House of Commons","To ask the hon. Member for Caithness, Sutherland and Easter Ross representing the House of Commons Commission, pursuant to the Answer of 18 March 2015 to Question 227498, to which budget the mobile charges for hon. Members' iPads fall; what plans the Commission has to offer hon. Members a platform other than iOS; and what provision PICT is making for hon. Members who do not wish to use iPads.","false","Biography information for Chi Onwurah","Newcastle upon Tyne Central","Chi Onwurah","228501"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/228620","Department for International Development","false","2015-03-24","<p>DFID does not currently fund the Plant for Peace programme. DFID’s education funding is focused on improving opportunities within Afghanistan itself, in line with the Afghan Government’s own priorities.</p><p> </p>","Putney","Justine Greening",,"2015-03-24T16:03:06.853Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/228620/answer","Biography information for Justine Greening","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/228620/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/228620/answer",,,,,"20","International Development","International Development","2015-03-19","Afghanistan","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for International Development, what steps her Department (a) has taken and (b) plans to take in respect of (i) funding the Plant for Peace pomegranate cultivation programme in Afghanistan and (ii) supporting Afghan nationals to take up educational opportunities in the UK; and if she will make a statement.","false","Biography information for Dr Julian Lewis","New Forest East","Dr Julian Lewis","228515"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/228621","Department for International Development","false","2015-03-24","<p>DFID does not hold this information in the form requested.</p><p> </p>","Putney","Justine Greening",,"2015-03-24T16:02:53.327Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/228621/answer","Biography information for Justine Greening","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/228621/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/228621/answer",,,,,"20","International Development","International Development","2015-03-19","Consultants","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for International Development, which 10 consultancies have received the largest amount from herDepartment since 2010; and how much her Department paid each such consultancy.","false","Biography information for Mary Creagh","Wakefield","Mary Creagh","228468"
