28433"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/228623","Department for International Development","false","2015-03-24","<p>The UK supports low-income countries to develop robust healthcare systems, including country efforts to build and maintain health worker capacity through training new health workers, building skills in existing health workers, and supporting government planning. The UK has provided bilateral health aid to over 30 countries and a number of regional programmes since May 2010, full details of which can be found at <a href="http://www.gov.uk/government/organisations/department-for-international-development/about/statistics" target="_blank">www.gov.uk/government/organisations/department-for-international-development/about/statistics</a>.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p>The UK has a number of targeted programmes that address critical health worker issues in Ethiopia, Pakistan, Nigeria, Zambia, Malawi, Sierra Leone, India, South Africa and Nepal. The UK also funds the Health Partnership Scheme (HPS) that supports partnerships between UK and developing country health institutions to strengthen health workforce capacity. The HPS supports activities in 26 countries in Africa and Asia.</p><p> </p>","New Forest West","Mr Desmond Swayne",,"2015-03-24T17:12:35.717Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/228623/answer","Biography information for Sir Desmond Swayne","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/228623/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/228623/answer",,,,,"20","International Development","International Development","2015-03-19","Developing Countries: Health Professions","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for International Development, which countries her Department has supported to train, recruit and retain health workers since May 2010.","false","Biography information for Debbie Abrahams","Oldham East and Saddleworth","Debbie Abrahams","228395"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/228624","Department for International Development","false","2015-03-24","<p>DFID does not hold this information in the form requested.</p><p> </p>","Putney","Justine Greening",,"2015-03-24T16:01:47.103Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/228624/answer","Biography information for Justine Greening","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/228624/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/228624/answer",,,,,"20","International Development","International Development","2015-03-19","Consultants","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for International Development, how much has been paid to consultancies for (a) programme delivery and (b) monitoring and evaluation by her Department in each year since 2010.","false","Biography information for Mary Creagh","Wakefield","Mary Creagh","228430"
