"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/228670","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2015-03-24","<p /> <p>The table below shows the number of reminder letters that have been issued giving one months warning of case closure. The case closure process started on the 30 June 2014, with reminder letters being issued from December 2014.</p><p> </p><p> </p><table><tbody><tr><td><p>Month</p></td><td><p>Notifications Issued in Month</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>December 2014</p></td><td><p>5,300</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>January 2015</p></td><td><p>13,200</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>February 2015</p></td><td><p>37,500</p></td></tr></tbody></table><p> </p><p> </p><p>Notes:</p><p>Figure rounded to the nearest 100.</p><p>The figures are made up from cases proactively selected for case closure, and those where an application has been made to the 2012 scheme and a case exists on the 93/03 scheme which is then reactively closed down.</p>","Thornbury and Yate","Steve Webb",,"2015-03-24T09:00:13.57Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/228670/answer","Biography information for Steve Webb","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/228670/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/228670/answer",,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2015-03-19","Children: Maintenance","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, how many reminder letters giving one month's warning of case closure have been sent to Child Support Agency customers in each of the last 12 months.","false","Biography information for Helen Goodman","Bishop Auckland","Helen Goodman","228462"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/228671","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2015-03-24","<p /> <p>Peer Reviews provide a thorough review of complex cases and any recommendations that arise are referred to the appropriate team. We cannot release the outcomes/information about peer reviews as they contain private information about individuals.</p>","Wirral West","Esther McVey","228499","2015-03-24T14:14:51.507Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/228671/answer","Biography information for Esther McVey","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/228671/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/228671/answer",,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2015-03-19","Reviews","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, pursuant to the Answer of 11 March 2015 to Question 226586, whether his Department's review of complex cases where claimants died has identified cases in which his Department's processes were not followed; and for each such case what recommendations for improvement have been made.","false","Biography information for Debbie Abrahams","Oldham East and Saddleworth","Debbie Abrahams","228498"
