n in the amount of (a) employment and support allowance and (b) other incapacity benefit paid in each month since May 2013.","false","Biography information for Stephen Timms","East Ham","Stephen Timms","228514"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/228674","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2015-03-24","<p /> <p>The available information on average (median) waiting times, at a national level, has been published and is available from the Personal Independence Payment statistics home page: <a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/collections/personal-independence-payment-statistics" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/collections/personal-independence-payment-statistics</a>. The requested level of disaggregation could only be obtained at disproportionate cost.</p>","Forest of Dean","Mr Mark Harper",,"2015-03-24T17:53:19.973Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/228674/answer","Biography information for Mr Mark Harper","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/228674/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/228674/answer",,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2015-03-19","Personal Independence Payment: Halton","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, how many people in Halton constituency waited more than (a) one month, (b) three and (c) six months for a decision on their personal independence payment claim in the last three years.","false","Biography information for Derek Twigg","Halton","Derek Twigg","228491"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/228675","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2015-03-23","<p>The last time a DWP Minister visited Scotland was in 2014.</p>","Thornbury and Yate","Steve Webb",,"2015-03-23T15:07:34.32Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/228675/answer","Biography information for Steve Webb","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/228675/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/228675/answer",,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2015-03-19","Scotland","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, when was the last time a Minister in his Department visited Scotland.","false","Biography information for Pamela Nash","Airdrie and Shotts","Pamela Nash","228385"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/228676","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2015-03-26","<p>It has not proved possible to respond to the hon. Member in the time available before Prorogation.</p>","Forest of Dean","Mr Mark Harper",,"2015-03-26T16:15:53.087Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/228676/answer","Biography information for Mr Mark Harper","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/228676/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/228676/answer",,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2015-03-19","Access to Work Programme","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, what the cost of the Access to Work scheme in (a) Airdrie and Shotts constituency, (b) North Lanarkshire, (c) Scotland and (d) the UK has been in each month since May 2010.","false","Biography information for Pamela Nash","Airdrie and Shotts","Pamela Nash","228369"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/228677","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2015-03-24","<p /> <p>A trial was held during the autumn of 2014 when claimants were sent text reminder messages of their assessment appointments. Following evaluation of that trial discussions were held with the new Health Assessment Advisory Service provider - Centre for Health and Disability Assessments (operated by MAXIMUS) – and the intention is to introduce the service nationally later in the year.</p>","Forest of Dean","Mr Mark Harper",,"2015-03-24T17:53:22.187Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/228677/answer","Biography information for Mr Mark Harper","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/228677/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/228677/answer",,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2015-03-19","Work Capability Assessment","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, what plans he has to introduce text or email notifications for claimants of the employment and support allowance required to attend a medical assessment.","false","Biography information for Sir Mark Hendrick","Preston","Mark Hendrick","228377"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/228678","HM Treasury","false","2015-03-25","<p>HMRC does not collect this information and therefore cannot say how many people in Preston have been contacted.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p>","Witham","Priti Patel",,"2015-03-25T11:41:13.273Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/228678/answer","Biography information for Priti Patel","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/228678/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/228678/answer",,,,,"14","Treasury","Treasury","2015-03-19","Welfare Tax Credits: Preston","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, how many people have been contacted by (a) Sigma, (b) Rossendales and (c) other debt collection agencies instructed by HM Revenue and Customs to collect overpaid tax credits in Preston constituency in the last 12 months.","false","Biography information for Sir Mark Hendrick","Preston","Mark Hendrick","228374"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/228679","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2015-03-24","<p /> <p>The Department is committed to reducing the time taken between claim and assessment for claimants of Employment and Support Allowance. The recent appointment of Centre for Health and Disability Assessments (operated by MAXIMUS) is integral to bringing improvement into the process as they bring both clinical expertise and a fresh approach that, over time, will significantly reduce waiting times and provide a better experience for claimants.</p>","Forest of Dean","Mr Mark Harper",,"2015-03-24T18:11:30.467Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/228679/answer","Biography information for Mr Mark Harper","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/228679/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/228679/answer",,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2015-03-19","Work Capability Assessment","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, what recent estimate he has made of the average time between a claim being made for employment and support allowance and the claimant receiving a work capability assessment.","false","Biography information for Jessica Morden","Newport East","Jessica Morden","228323"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/228680","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2015-03-25","<p /> <p>As part of the Government’s transparency agenda, a redacted version of the MAXIMUS Health and Human Services Ltd contract with the Department for Work and Pensions to deliver Health and Disability Assessments was published on the Contracts Finder website on 24 November 2014. This can be accessed at:</p><p> </p><p><a href="https://online.contractsfinder.businesslink.gov.uk/Common/View%20Notice.aspx?site=1000&amp;lang=en&amp;noticeid=1644334&amp;fs=true" target="_blank">https://online.contractsfinder.businesslink.gov.uk/Common/View%20Notice.aspx?site=1000&amp;lang=en&amp;noticeid=1644334&amp;fs=true</a></p><p> </p><p>The Department has put in place a strong contract management and operational monitoring regime so that we will be able to hold the supplier to account in the event of under-performance. However, we are confident that we have selected the right provider for this service and we look forward to the delivery of a high quality service. The contract makes clear in what circumstances financial remedies will be incurred if performance does not meet the expected levels, as well as the other non-financial remedies available, up to and including termination. The Department has both Contract and Performance Managers in place for the contract who help ensure that all aspects of the contract are delivered, policy objectives are met and that performance is rigorously managed.</p><p> </p><p>Centre for Health and Disability Assessments (operated by MAXIMUS) has not been allocated specific targets relating to the clearance of legacy work.</p><p>The Department and Centre for Health and Disability Assessments are committed to a close partnership, working to continuously improve waiting times for all assessment appointments.</p>","Forest of Dean","Mr Mark Harper",,"2015-03-25T16:35:12.36Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/228680/answer","Biography information for Mr Mark Harper","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/228680/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/228680/answer","Forest of Dean","Mr Mark Harper","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/228680/answer/previousversion/52575","Biography information for Mr Mark Harper","29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2015-03-19","MAXMIMUS Health and Human Services","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, if he will place in the Library a copy of the service level agreement with Maximus relating to work capability assessments; what penalties exist under that agreement for a failure to adhere to the terms of the agreement; and what requirements exist under that agreement for the clearance of the backlog of existing cases.","false","Biography information for Jessica Morden","Newport East","Jessica Morden","228324"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/228681","HM Treasury","false","2015-03-26","<p>The effect of alcohol consumption is referred to in the policy costing note on alcohol duties published at Budget 2015, available at the gov.uk website<sup><sup>[1]</sup></sup>.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p>[1] <a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/uploads/system/uploads/attachment_data/file/413895/Policy_Costings_18_00.pdf" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/uploads/system/uploads/attachment_data/file/413895/Policy_Costings_18_00.pdf</a>.</p><p> </p>",,"Lord Deighton",,"2015-03-26T14:11:59.143Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/228681/answer","Biography information for Lord Deighton","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/228681/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/228681/answer",,,,,"14","Treasury","Treasury","2015-03-19","Alcoholic Drinks: Excise Duties","2","House of Lords","To ask Her Majesty’s Government what is their estimate of likely changes in alcohol consumption in the United Kingdom as a result of changes to alcohol duty in the 2015 Budget.","false","Biography information for Baroness Hayter of Kentish Town",,"Baroness Hayter of Kentish Town","HL5863"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/228682","HM Treasury","false","2015-03-26","<p>The government recognises the health and social harms associated with those who consume excess alcohol. The government has therefore taken targeted action through the alcohol duty system to encourage responsible alcohol consumption. For example, the government increased duty on super strength lager.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p>The Government is also taking other action to reduce alcohol related harms. This includes the creation of 20 Local Alcohol Action Areas with the aim of reducing alcohol health and crime harms by encouraging partnerships between industry, local agencies and the voluntary sector. Licensing changes have also been made to help tackle irresponsible alcohol consumption. For example, Local Councils have been given the ability to collect a Late Night Levy from alcohol retailers to contribute towards the cost of policing.</p><p> </p>",,"Lord Deighton",,"2015-03-26T13:52:13.703Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/228682/answer","Biography information for Lord Deighton","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/228682/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/228682/answer",,,,,"14","Treasury","Treasury","2015-03-19","Alcoholic Drinks: Excise Duties","2","House of Lords","To ask Her Majesty’s Government what action they plan to take to counter the expected increase in alcohol consumption following cuts in alcohol duty in the 2015 Budget, as implied by the HM Treasury Policy Costings calculations.","false","Biography information for Baroness Hayter of Kentish Town",,"Baroness Hayter of Kentish Town","HL5864"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/228683","Department of Health","false","2015-03-25","<p>The Care Quality Commission has created an interactive web-based map showing the location of designated health-based places of safety in England for people detained under section 136 of the Mental Health Act 1983:</p><p> </p><p><br> <a href="http://www.cqc.org.uk/content/map-health-based-places-safety-0" target="_blank">http://www.cqc.org.uk/content/map-health-based-places-safety-0</a></p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p>The current version shows 167 places of safety in England.</p><p> </p>",,"Earl Howe",,"2015-03-25T13:29:50.977Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/228683/answer","Biography information for Earl Howe","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/228683/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/228683/answer",,,,,"17","Health","Health","2015-03-19","Compulsorily Detained Psychiatric Patients","2","House of Lords","To ask Her Majesty’s Government how many places of safety have been provided under section 136 of the Mental Health Act 1983; and what assessment they have made of the geographic spread of such places.","false","Biography information for The Lord Bishop of Bristol",,"The Lord Bishop of Bristol","HL5865"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/228684","Department for Transport","false","2015-03-25","<p>There have been no general discussions between Her Majesty’s Government and Network Rail in relation to giving Network Rail additional compulsory purchase powers for the purposes mentioned. Her Majesty's Governmentand Network Rail from time to time discuss particular applications by Network Rail, under section 14 of the Railway Regulation Act 1842, in relation to obtaining temporary access to land neighbouring the railway, where this is needed for the purpose of certain safety works on the railway.</p><p> </p><p>Network Rail can also apply to Her Majesty's Government, under section 15 of that Act, for a revival of the compulsory purchase powers which would originally have applied under the enabling legislation for the relevant stretch of railway; again this would be where such acquisition is needed to be able to effect safety repairs and works. Each application by Network Rail under section 14 and 15 is considered on its specific facts and the safety issues arising.</p><p> </p><p>The powers of entry arising under section 14 of the 1842 Act were considered both by the Transport Resilience Review and the Powers of Entry Review under the Protection of Freedoms Act 2012. Following on from these Her Majesty's Government expects to consult with Network Rail and other stakeholders over a code of practice in relation to the use of section 14.</p><p> </p>",,"Baroness Kramer",,"2015-03-25T13:48:49.74Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/228684/answer","Biography information for Baroness Kramer","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/228684/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/228684/answer",,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2015-03-19","Network Rail","2","House of Lords","To ask Her Majesty’s Government what discussions they have had with Network Rail over giving the company compulsory purchase powers outside its permitted development rights to enable it to obtain access to its land or achieve small enhancements, maintenance and renewals more quickly and cheaply.","false","Biography information for Lord Berkeley",,"Lord Berkeley","HL5866"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/228685","Department for Culture Media and Sport","false","2015-03-26","<p>The Electronic Communications Code, set out in Schedule 2 to the Telecommunications Act 1984 and amended by the Communications Act 2003, enables electronic communications operators to place apparatus on land. Paragraph 5 offers recourse to the County Court (or the Sherriff’s Court in Scotland) for communications operators to apply for compulsory access to land subject to appropriate compensation and consideration being paid to the occupier of the land.</p><p>There are also provisions in Schedule 4 to the Communications Act 2003 which allow the compulsory acquisition of land by communications operators.</p>",,"Lord Bourne of Aberystwyth",,"2015-03-26T13:49:47.96Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/228685/answer","Biography information for Lord Bourne of Aberystwyth","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/228685/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/228685/answer",,,,,"10","Culture, Media and Sport","Culture, Media and Sport","2015-03-19","Mobile Phones","2","House of Lords","To ask Her Majesty’s Government what compulsory purchase rights mobile telephone companies have to enable them to erect or maintain their transmitters and other equipment.","false","Biography information for Lord Berkeley",,"Lord Berkeley","HL5867"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/228686","Department for Energy and Climate Change","false","2015-03-23","<p>DECC officials, working closely with Cornwall County Council, continue to engage with their German counterparts to explore research options for the potential testing of geothermal resources. The main exchanges have been through email correspondence and by telephone.</p>",,"Baroness Verma",,"2015-03-23T17:02:55.02Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/228686/answer","Biography information for Baroness Verma","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/228686/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/228686/answer",,,,,"63","Energy and Climate Change","Energy and Climate Change","2015-03-19","Geothermal Power: Research","2","House of Lords","To ask Her Majesty’s Government, further to the Written Answer by Lord Ahmad of Wimbledon on 18 March (HL5377), what action they are taking to progress discussions with the government of Germany following their letter to that government last year; and how many meetings between United Kingdom and German officials have taken place on this subject since then.","false","Biography information for Lord Berkeley",,"Lord Berkeley","HL5868"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/228687","Department for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","false","2015-03-25","<p>The NAO report considered the difference between publicly-funded investment and public-private partnerships, such as PFI. It describes the Government’s decision-making processes and summarises recent developments. The report does not draw conclusions about the Government’s record.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p>The Thames Tideway Tunnel is a private sector project of a scale and complexity unique to the UK water industry. The Government issued the Strategic Case for the Tunnel (“Creating a River Thames Fit for our Future”) in November 2011, and the need for a tunnel was confirmed by Parliament in March 2012 when the Waste Water National Policy Statement was approved. The Government confirmed in a Written Ministerial Statement on 5 June 2014 (<em>Official Report</em>, column 11WS) that it would, subject to State Aid clearance, offer a contingent financial support package to the winner of the procurement for an Infrastructure Provider to finance and deliver the Thames Tideway Tunnel currently being undertaken by Thames Water. The Government continues to judge that the project will be value for money for taxpayers and customers who will be directly funding the Tunnel, and that an Infrastructure Provider procured by Thames Water is the preferred route for delivering the project.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p>",,"Lord De Mauley",,"2015-03-25T15:43:25.52Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/228687/answer","Biography information for Lord De Mauley","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/228687/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/228687/answer",,,,,"13","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","2015-03-19","Thames Tideway Tunnel","2","House of Lords","To ask Her Majesty’s Government whether they consider that the Thames Tideway Tunnel project provides value for money, in the light of the National Audit Office’s Report "The choice of finance for capital investment" published on 18 March.","false","Biography information for Lord Berkeley",,"Lord Berkeley","HL5869"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/228688","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2015-03-24","<p /> <p>We welcome the Supreme Court ruling that the benefit cap is lawful. The Court decided that the benefit cap does not breach the European Convention on Human rights and does not unlawfully discriminate against lone parents.</p>",,"Lord Freud",,"2015-03-24T13:42:44.543Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/228688/answer","Biography information for Lord Freud","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/228688/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/228688/answer",,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2015-03-19","Social Security Benefits","2","House of Lords","To ask Her Majesty’s Government what assessment they have made of the Supreme Court judgment of 1 March regarding the benefits cap.","false","Biography information for Baroness King of Bow",,"Baroness King of Bow","HL5870"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/228689","Department for Communities and Local Government","false","2015-03-26","<p>I am placing a copy of the Department for Communities and Local Government’s written submission in the case of Nzolameso v City of Westminster in the Library of the House. The Department's submission reflects our long-standing policy practice and guidance. We await the full judgment on this specific case.</p><p> </p><p> </p>",,"Lord Ahmad of Wimbledon",,"2015-03-26T13:12:51.223Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/228689/answer","Biography information for Lord Ahmad of Wimbledon","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/228689/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/228689/answer",,,,,"7","Communities and Local Government","Communities and Local Government","2015-03-19","Council Housing: City of Westminster","2","House of Lords","To ask Her Majesty’s Government whether they will place in the Library of the House a copy of the written submission from the Department for Communities and Local Government to the Supreme Court in support of Titian Nzolameso’s appeal against Westminster City Council’s decision to offer her accommodation near Milton Keynes.","false","Biography information for Baroness King of Bow",,"Baroness King of Bow","HL5871"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/228690","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2015-03-26","<p /> <p>The Department for Work and Pensions does not have a clearance time target nor does it have information about average clearance times.</p><p> </p><p>It plans to introduce a clearance time target for all benefits, starting with ESA from April 2016.</p><p> </p><p>It plans to incorporate information on mandatory reconsideration clearance times into the relevant existing regular statistical publications. However, before decisions are made DWP statisticians need to make sure that the data is accurate and fit for purpose. When a decision has been made and as each publication is ready, we will pre-announce the improvements in accordance with the UKSA release protocols.</p>",,"Lord Freud","HL5873","2015-03-26T12:43:31.203Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/228690/answer","Biography information for Lord Freud","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/228690/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/228690/answer",,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2015-03-19","Personal Independence Payment","2","House of Lords","To ask Her Majesty’s Government what is the target time in which the Department for Work and Pensions aims to process mandatory reconsiderations for Personal Independence Payment applications.","false","Biography information for Baroness King of Bow",,"Baroness King of Bow","HL5872"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/228691","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2015-03-26","<p>The Department for Work and Pensions does not have a clearance time target nor does it have information about average clearance times.</p><p> </p><p>It plans to introduce a clearance time target for all benefits, starting with ESA from April 2016.</p><p> </p><p>It plans to incorporate information on mandatory reconsideration clearance times into the relevant existing regular statistical publications. However, before decisions are made DWP statisticians need to make sure that the data is accurate and fit for purpose. When a decision has been made and as each publication is ready, we will pre-announce the improvements in accordance with the UKSA release protocols.</p>",,"Lord Freud","HL5872","2015-03-26T12:43:31.093Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/228691/answer","Biography information for Lord Freud","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/228691/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/228691/answer",,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2015-03-19","Personal Independence Payment","2","House of Lords","To ask Her Majesty’s Government what is the average clearance time for Personal Independence Payment mandatory reconsiderations.","false","Biography information for Baroness King of Bow",,"Baroness King of Bow","HL5873"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/228692","Department for Communities and Local Government","false","2015-03-25","<p>I refer the noble Lady to the answer given by my rt Hon Friend the former Minister of State for Housing (Grant Shapps) on 25 June 2012, <em>Official Report</em>, column 680W.</p><p> </p>",,"Lord Ahmad of Wimbledon",,"2015-03-25T14:14:14.687Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/228692/answer","Biography information for Lord Ahmad of Wimbledon","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/228692/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/228692/answer",,,,,"7","Communities and Local Government","Communities and Local Government","2015-03-19","Homelessness: Tower Hamlets","2","House of Lords","To ask Her Majesty’s Government, further to the Written Answer by Lord Ahmad of Wimbledon on 9 March (HL5059), whether they will place in the Library of the House copies of their correspondence with the London Borough of Tower Hamlets about the number of homeless families with children in bed and breakfast accommodation beyond the six week limit.","false","Biography information for Baroness King of Bow",,"Baroness King of Bow","HL5874"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/228693","Department for Communities and Local Government","false","2015-03-26","<p>As set out in the Written Ministerial Statement on 18 September 2012, <em>Official Report</em>, column 32WS, the Department no longer publishes statistics at a regional level. This follows the abolition of regional government by the Coalition, which does not believe that regions provide a coherent or meaningful framework for assessing public policy. Instead, our published statistics present, where relevant, other sub-national geographies which are more aligned with public policy.</p><p> </p><p>This Government is committed to preventing and tackling homelessness. We have increased homelessness prevention spending, making over £500 million available since 2010 to local authorities and the voluntary sector to help the most vulnerable in society. Homelessness remains lower than in 26 of the last 30 years. It is around half the average level it was under the previous Administration.</p><p> </p>",,"Lord Ahmad of Wimbledon",,"2015-03-26T13:08:28.213Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/228693/answer","Biography information for Lord Ahmad of Wimbledon","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/228693/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/228693/answer",,,,,"7","Communities and Local Government","Communities and Local Government","2015-03-19","Homelessness","2","House of Lords","To ask Her Majesty’s Government whether they will resume the publication of homelessness statistical "live table" 783 giving details of the number of homeless households in each type of temporary accommodation by region.","false","Biography information for Baroness King of Bow",,"Baroness King of Bow","HL5875"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/228694","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","false","2015-03-26","<p>The UK continues to support the Intergovernmental Authority on Development’s (IGAD) efforts to end the crisis in South Sudan. The UK has provided financial, expertise and political support to IGAD through diplomatic engagement as part of the Troika (UK, US and Norway).</p>",,"Baroness Anelay of St Johns",,"2015-03-26T13:00:50.39Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/228694/answer","Biography information for Baroness Anelay of St Johns","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/228694/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/228694/answer",,,,,"16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2015-03-19","South Sudan","2","House of Lords","To ask Her Majesty’s Government whether the Intergovernmental Authority on Development remains the key process for political dialogue in South Sudan; and what recent diplomatic efforts the United Kingdom has made towards achieving a peaceful settlement through the Intergovernmental Authority on Development and other organisations.","false","Biography information for The Earl of Sandwich",,"The Earl of Sandwich","HL5876"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/228695","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","false","2015-03-26","<p>Church leaders in South Sudan are influential and have played an important role in reconciliation efforts to date. They will have a key part to play in future national reconciliation processes. The UK is engaging with different reconciliation mechanisms as well as funding technical support.</p><p> </p>",,"Baroness Anelay of St Johns",,"2015-03-26T12:52:44.68Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/228695/answer","Biography information for Baroness Anelay of St Johns","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/228695/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/228695/answer",,,,,"16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2015-03-19","South Sudan","2","House of Lords","To ask Her Majesty’s Government what progress has been made towards peace and reconciliation through the churches and specialised voluntary agencies in South Sudan; and what plans there are for the United Kingdom to support those initiatives.","false","Biography information for The Earl of Sandwich",,"The Earl of Sandwich","HL5877"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/228696","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","false","2015-03-26","<p>The UK has consistently emphasised the importance of inclusivity in South Sudan’s peace process. We will continue to engage with civil society and faith leaders to ensure their voices are heard in the peace talks.</p>",,"Baroness Anelay of St Johns",,"2015-03-26T12:51:49.39Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/228696/answer","Biography information for Baroness Anelay of St Johns","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/228696/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/228696/answer",,,,,"16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2015-03-19","South Sudan","2","House of Lords","To ask Her Majesty’s Government what contributions the United Kingdom will make to the encouragement of civil society and cultural exchanges to help restore confidence in South Sudan during 2015.","false","Biography information for The Earl of Sandwich",,"The Earl of Sandwich","HL5878"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/228697","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","false","2015-03-26","<p>We are deeply disappointed with the lack of progress on National Dialogue in Sudan since it was announced by the President in January 2014. National dialogue, if genuine, inclusive and comprehensive, offers the best hope for the Sudanese parties to secure peace for their country. We welcome recent pledges by the Government of Sudan and Sudanese opposition groups to participate in a “pre-dialogue” meeting.</p><p>We continue to support the voluntary sector. Our Embassy in Khartoum is working to strengthen the democratic environment by increasing our work with civil society.</p><p> </p>",,"Baroness Anelay of St Johns",,"2015-03-26T12:50:50.607Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/228697/answer","Biography information for Baroness Anelay of St Johns","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/228697/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/228697/answer",,,,,"16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2015-03-19","Sudan","2","House of Lords","To ask Her Majesty’s Government what assessment they have made of the current status of the National Dialogue in Sudan; and what plans they have for the United Kingdom to contribute more to the democratic process there through the voluntary sector.","false","Biography information for The Earl of Sandwich",,"The Earl of Sandwich","HL5879"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/228698","Ministry of Defence","false","2015-03-25","<p>The UK's ex-Service community is largely elderly; almost half are over age 75 and 64% are over age 65. It is important that this country meets their needs, just as they answered the needs of their country; meeting the call of the nation during the First and Second World Wars, through national service, voluntary enlistment and the reserve forces.</p><p>To support this community, £5 million of LIBOR funding has been made available every year for the next five years for any UK veterans who are surviving World War Two veterans, those who undertook National Service and other voluntary enlisted veterans who, by virtue of their age, may need some focused support in relation to their health and social care needs.</p><p>The funds will not provide benevolence payments to individuals. Charities can bid for money to provide practical support and/or companionship to this group of veterans to improve their wellbeing. This might also include projects to build or enhance access to centres where elderly veterans can meet, or to promote the education of elderly veterans' needs, research and other support mechanisms.</p><p>The Ministry of Defence intends to administer the fund through a dedicated grant scheme. The terms of this scheme are being developed and will be announced in due course.</p>",,"Lord Astor of Hever",,"2015-03-25T17:36:09.267Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/228698/answer","Biography information for Lord Astor of Hever","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/228698/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/228698/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2015-03-19","Veterans: Northern Ireland","2","House of Lords","To ask Her Majesty’s Government whether army veterans based in Northern Ireland will benefit from the £25 million healthcare fund for aged veterans announced in the Budget, and if so, how.","false","Biography information for Lord Empey",,"Lord Empey","HL5880"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/228699","Department for Energy and Climate Change","false","2015-03-24","<p>The UK agrees that the Energy Community has an important role to play in the energy security of the EU and neighbouring countries and that the Energy Community has been an effective vehicle for encouraging countries in the EU near neighbourhood to align themselves with the EU energy networks.</p><p>The UK ensures that it takes all opportunities to influence the direction of EU policy towards the Energy Community. This is normally achieved through contributions to discussions at official-level meetings in Brussels, where the EU’s policy towards the Energy Community is agreed.</p>",,"Baroness Verma",,"2015-03-24T16:13:53.697Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/228699/answer","Biography information for Baroness Verma","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/228699/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/228699/answer",,,,,"63","Energy and Climate Change","Energy and Climate Change","2015-03-19","Energy Community","2","House of Lords","To ask Her Majesty’s Government, further to the Written Answers by Baroness Verma on 18 March (HL5568 to HL5572), whether, in view of the Energy Community's aims in respect of enhancing security of supply, attracting investment in power generation and networks, and reducing dependence upon Russian supplies of gas, they consider that the United Kingdom should increase the level of its participation in the various institutions of the Energy Community as it is entitled to do as a participant; and at which meetings the views of the United Kingdom on the issues to be considered by the various institutions and groups of the Energy Community are discussed within the European Union to ensure that the United Kingdom's position is reflected by the European Union representatives at the meetings at which the United Kingdom does not participate.","false","Biography information for Lord Bowness",,"Lord Bowness","HL5881"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/228700","Department of Health","false","2015-03-26","<p>In 2014, the National Institute for Health and Care Excellence (NICE) published updated guidelines on the management of atrial fibrillation (AF), which covers the diagnosis, assessment and treatment of the condition. NICE is also developing AF Quality Standards which it expects to publish this summer.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p>In addition, the NHS Health Check programme’s best practice guidance recommends that a pulse check is carried out as part of the process of taking a blood pressure reading and that individuals who are found to have an irregular pulse rhythm should be referred to their general practitioner (GP) for further investigation.</p><p> </p><p><strong> </strong></p><p> </p><p>NHS Improving Quality’s (NHS IQ) is also taking action on AF. It is promoting the use of GRASP-AF (Guidance on Risk Assessment and Stroke Prevention for Atrial Fibrillation) within GP practices in England. GRASP-AF is a simple and effective audit tool developed by and trialled in the National Health Service, which greatly simplifies the process of identifying patients with AF who are not receiving the right management to help reduce their risk of stroke. NHS IQ is currently collaborating with partner organisations, including charities, to support the nationwide roll-out of GRASP-AF.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p>To support this work, NHS IQ recently published an analysis of the costs and benefits of using the anticoagulant drug warfarin to help prevent stroke in people with AF. A copy of this analysis is attached and can also be found at:</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p><a href="http://www.nhsiq.nhs.uk/media/2566750/af_economic_analysis_final.pdf" target="_blank">http://www.nhsiq.nhs.uk/media/2566750/af_economic_analysis_final.pdf</a></p><p> </p>",,"Earl Howe",,"2015-03-26T12:28:50.587Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/228700/answer","Biography information for Earl Howe","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/228700/answer","Warfarin analysis.pdf","Warfarin analysis.pdf","Warfarin costs and benefits analysis","Warfarin costs and benefits analysis","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/228700/answer",,,,,"17","Health","Health","2015-03-19","Heart Diseases","2","House of Lords","To ask Her Majesty’s Government what recent steps they have taken to improve the diagnosis and management of atrial fibrillation.","false","Biography information for Lord Black of Brentwood",,"Lord Black of Brentwood","HL5882"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/228701","Ministry of Defence","false","2015-03-23","<p>Any files relating to the West Wales sighting in 1977 will be held by the National Archives. Consequently, the Ministry of Defence holds no information on this incident.</p>",,"Lord Astor of Hever",,"2015-03-23T17:24:58.563Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/228701/answer","Biography information for Lord Astor of Hever","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/228701/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/228701/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2015-03-19","Unidentified Flying Objects: Wales","2","House of Lords","To ask Her Majesty’s Government whether the Provost and Security Services conducted an investigation into sightings of unidentified flying objects in West Wales during 1977.","false","Biography information for Lord Black of Brentwood",,"Lord Black of Brentwood","HL5883"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/228702","Cabinet Office","false","2015-03-25","<p>The information requested falls within the responsibility of the UK Statistics Authority. I have asked the Authority to reply.</p><p> </p>",,"Lord Wallace of Saltaire",,"2015-03-25T13:54:29.833Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/228702/answer","Biography information for Lord Wallace of Saltaire","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/228702/answer","HL5884 ONS Reply.pdf","HL5884 ONS Reply.pdf","ONS Letter to PEER - Civil Partnerships","ONS Letter to PEER - Civil Partnerships","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/228702/answer",,,,,"53","Cabinet Office","Cabinet Office","2015-03-19","Civil Partnerships","2","House of Lords","To ask Her Majesty’s Government how many civil partnerships have been registered since the commencement of the Marriage (Same Sex Couples) Act 2013.","false","Biography information for Lord Black of Brentwood",,"Lord Black of Brentwood","HL5884"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/228703","Home Office","false","2015-03-24","<p>The UK Border Agency was abolished in March 2013. The Government is supportive of Eurostar’s plans for new services between Southern France and London commencing in May 2015 and between Amsterdam and London from December 2016.<br><br>The operating model for these new Eurostar services makes provision for a stop at Lille or Brussels to allow for physical security, Schengen exit and UK entry checks to be completed. This was a commercial decision made by Eurostar which is satisfactory in terms of UK border control requirements.</p><p> </p>",,"Lord Bates",,"2015-03-24T14:59:55.507Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/228703/answer","Biography information for Lord Bates","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/228703/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/228703/answer",,,,,"1","Home Office","Home Office","2015-03-19","Eurostar","2","House of Lords","To ask Her Majesty’s Government, further to the Written Answer by Baroness Kramer on 16 March (HL5635), whether their support for Eurostar's plans for new services means that the concerns of the Border Agency have been resolved without requiring passengers to change trains en route.","false","Biography information for Lord Bradshaw",,"Lord Bradshaw","HL5885"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/228704","Department for Transport","false","2015-03-23","<p>It would be premature to make any judgements around the causes of the fire until the independent statutory investigations by the Rail Accident Investigation Branch (RAIB) and its French counterpart, BEA-TT have been completed.</p>",,"Baroness Kramer",,"2015-03-23T13:55:51.387Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/228704/answer","Biography information for Baroness Kramer","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/228704/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/228704/answer",,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2015-03-19","Channel Tunnel: Fires","2","House of Lords","To ask Her Majesty’s Government, further to the Written Answer by Baroness Kramer on 16 March (HL5636) whether the likely cause of the fire in the Channel Tunnel in January was an aerial on a lorry coming into contact with the overhead electric power equipment; and whether they consider that the fire could have been avoided if the lorry had been conveyed in a closed wagon.","false","Biography information for Lord Bradshaw",,"Lord Bradshaw","HL5886"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/228705","Department for Business, Innovation and Skills","false","2015-03-25","<p>The Government expects companies to comply with the requirements of the Reports on Payments to Government Regulations 2014.</p><p> </p><p>The Regulations, which came into effect on 1 December 2014, set out the enforcement and penalty regime for any company that fails to comply in part or in full. It is a matter for the company to ensure that it is fully complying with the requirements. On a criminal conviction for not doing so the penalty may be a fine or a term of imprisonment for the directors of the company.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p>Reports made annually by companies under these Regulations will be published on Companies House website where both government and other interested parties will be able to consider the reports and their accuracy.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p>",,"Baroness Neville-Rolfe",,"2015-03-25T13:24:18.49Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/228705/answer","Biography information for Baroness Neville-Rolfe","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/228705/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/228705/answer",,,,,"26","Business, Innovation and Skills","Business, Innovation and Skills","2015-03-19","Reports on Payments to Governments Regulations 2014","2","House of Lords","To ask Her Majesty’s Government what measures they will take against extractives industry companies which seek to subvert the intention behind the Reports on Payments to Governments Regulations 2014.","false","Biography information for The Lord Bishop of Worcester",,"The Lord Bishop of Worcester","HL5887"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/228706","Department for Business, Innovation and Skills","false","2015-03-25","<p>The Government expects companies to comply with the requirements of the Reports on Payments to Government Regulations 2014.</p><p> </p><p>The Regulations, which came into effect on 1 December 2014, set out the enforcement and penalty regime for any company that fails to comply in part or in full. It is a matter for the company to ensure that it is fully complying with the requirements. On a criminal conviction for not doing so the penalty may be a fine or a term of imprisonment for the directors of the company.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p>Reports made annually by companies under these Regulations will be published on Companies House website where both government and other interested parties will be able to consider the reports and their accuracy.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p>",,"Baroness Neville-Rolfe",,"2015-03-25T13:22:07.827Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/228706/answer","Biography information for Baroness Neville-Rolfe","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/228706/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/228706/answer",,,,,"26","Business, Innovation and Skills","Business, Innovation and Skills","2015-03-19","Reports on Payments to Governments Regulations 2014","2","House of Lords","To ask Her Majesty’s Government what measures they will take to ensure that United Kingdom extractives industry companies do not interpret the requirements of the Reports on Payments to Governments Regulations 2014 in a way that will enable corrupt payments in resource-rich countries to stay hidden.","false","Biography information for The Lord Bishop of Worcester",,"The Lord Bishop of Worcester","HL5888"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/228707","Department for Business, Innovation and Skills","false","2015-03-25","<p>Any guidance that is produced by industry is for the use of the companies within that sector.</p><p> </p><p>Any company completing a report on payments made to government must be confident that they have met the requirements of the regulations and where appropriate taken independent legal advice.</p><p> </p>",,"Baroness Neville-Rolfe",,"2015-03-25T13:26:56.743Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/228707/answer","Biography information for Baroness Neville-Rolfe","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/228707/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/228707/answer",,,,,"26","Business, Innovation and Skills","Business, Innovation and Skills","2015-03-19","Reports on Payments to Governments Regulations 2014","2","House of Lords","To ask Her Majesty’s Government whether they will endorse the United Kingdom extractives industry’s guidance on the Reports on Payments to Governments Regulations 2014 if that guidance could in any way enable corrupt payments in resource-rich countries to stay hidden.","false","Biography information for The Lord Bishop of Worcester",,"The Lord Bishop of Worcester","HL5889"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/228708","Department for Business, Innovation and Skills","false","2015-03-26","<p>We listen to the views of all stakeholders. As well as replying to correspondence from civil society on this matter, the Minister listened to views during a conference call with representatives from the Publish What You Pay coalition this week.</p><p> </p><p>Officials met civil society representatives on four occasions to hear views on industry guidance and considered a number of written representations, including a copy of the Publish What You Pay response to the public consultation exercise undertaken by industry associations.</p><p> </p>",,"Baroness Neville-Rolfe",,"2015-03-26T14:57:03.763Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/228708/answer","Biography information for Baroness Neville-Rolfe","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/228708/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/228708/answer",,,,,"26","Business, Innovation and Skills","Business, Innovation and Skills","2015-03-19","Reports on Payments to Governments Regulations 2014","2","House of Lords","To ask Her Majesty’s Government what steps they will take to listen to the views of civil society before endorsing any guidance from United Kingdom extractives industry companies on the Reports on Payments to Governments Regulations 2014.","false","Biography information for The Lord Bishop of Worcester",,"The Lord Bishop of Worcester","HL5890"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/228709","Department of Health","false","2015-03-25","<p>The UK National Screening Committee makes recommendations on whole population screening programmes. It is for the National Institute for Health and Care Excellence or its accredited guideline producing bodies to recommend care and testing of people at high risk.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p>NHS England has commissioning arrangements in place for carrier testing for Tay Sachs disease for at risk populations. Genetic testing will be undertaken where there is a known family history, which indicates a risk of the specific condition or in response to the individual’s clinical symptoms. In the absence of a family history or clinical symptoms it is the responsibility of clinical commissioning groups based on their local needs as to whether they fund referrals to clinical genetics for carrier screening for Tay Sachs disease.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p>Genomics offers a great opportunity to improve our insight into genetic diseases. It is for this reason that the Government launched a world-leading project to sequence 100,000 genomes from National Health Service patients and established Genomics England, a subsidiary of the Department, to deliver the project.</p><p> </p>",,"Earl Howe","HL5892 ; HL5893 ; HL5894","2015-03-25T14:05:28.233Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/228709/answer","Biography information for Earl Howe","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/228709/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/228709/answer",,,,,"17","Health","Health","2015-03-19","Hereditary Diseases","2","House of Lords","To ask Her Majesty’s Government which organisation or body is responsible for assessing the needs of the local population for carrier screening for genetic disorders in at risk populations without an established family history.","false","Biography information for Baroness Deech",,"Baroness Deech","HL5891"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/228710","Department of Health","false","2015-03-25","<p>The UK National Screening Committee makes recommendations on whole population screening programmes. It is for the National Institute for Health and Care Excellence or its accredited guideline producing bodies to recommend care and testing of people at high risk.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p>NHS England has commissioning arrangements in place for carrier testing for Tay Sachs disease for at risk populations. Genetic testing will be undertaken where there is a known family history, which indicates a risk of the specific condition or in response to the individual’s clinical symptoms. In the absence of a family history or clinical symptoms it is the responsibility of clinical commissioning groups based on their local needs as to whether they fund referrals to clinical genetics for carrier screening for Tay Sachs disease.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p>Genomics offers a great opportunity to improve our insight into genetic diseases. It is for this reason that the Government launched a world-leading project to sequence 100,000 genomes from National Health Service patients and established Genomics England, a subsidiary of the Department, to deliver the project.</p><p> </p>",,"Earl Howe","HL5891 ; HL5893 ; HL5894","2015-03-25T14:05:28.34Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/228710/answer","Biography information for Earl Howe","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/228710/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/228710/answer",,,,,"17","Health","Health","2015-03-19","Tay-Sachs Disease","2","House of Lords","To ask Her Majesty’s Government what assessment they have made of provision in the National Health Service of carrier screening services for Tay Sachs disease in the Ashkenazi Jewish community since the change in national screening policy in April 2013.","false","Biography information for Baroness Deech",,"Baroness Deech","HL5892"
